1
00:01:28,772 --> 00:01:30,205
[Flames roar]

2
00:01:32,532 --> 00:01:33,851
[Sirens blare]

3
00:01:35,372 --> 00:01:36,885
[Tires screech]

4
00:01:39,452 --> 00:01:40,726
Riggs, Homicide.

5
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:42,245
COP: Nobody's dead.
RIGGS: The night's young.

6
00:01:42,332 --> 00:01:44,084
This is Sergeant Murtaugh.

7
00:01:44,172 --> 00:01:45,571
RIGGS: Threat or scare?
COP: Real thing.

8
00:01:45,652 --> 00:01:47,210
COP: He saw the device.

9
00:01:47,292 --> 00:01:50,364
MAN: It's on Level 1, by the gas pumps.
I wrote the license plate number.

10
00:01:50,452 --> 00:01:52,124
That's okay, sir. Thanks a lot.

11
00:01:52,212 --> 00:01:54,328
RIGGS: You evacuated the building?
COP: It's clean.

12
00:01:54,412 --> 00:01:55,845
ROGER: Where's the bomb squad?
COP: Coming.

13
00:01:55,932 --> 00:01:58,082
ROGER: Good. It's under control. Let's go.

14
00:01:58,172 --> 00:02:00,367
I think we ought to check this out.

15
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:02,811
ROGER: Riggs?
RIGGS: What?

16
00:02:02,892 --> 00:02:04,962
- Bomb squad's coming.
- There's no bomb!

17
00:02:05,052 --> 00:02:07,486
- How do you know?
- Because it's a full moon.

18
00:02:07,572 --> 00:02:09,767
Moon, lunar, lunatics. They're everywhere.

19
00:02:09,852 --> 00:02:11,808
RIGGS: Is that Greek?
ROGER: No, Latin.

20
00:02:11,892 --> 00:02:13,723
You surprise the shit out of me.

21
00:02:13,812 --> 00:02:16,087
There's no bomb.
It's probably a false alarm.

22
00:02:16,172 --> 00:02:18,686
It happens. He probably saw a radio
on the back seat.

23
00:02:18,772 --> 00:02:21,206
Let's not mess with it.
Wait for the bomb squad.

24
00:02:21,292 --> 00:02:24,045
You're right. You sit tight,
I'll be right back.

25
00:02:24,572 --> 00:02:26,130
What's the matter with you?

26
00:02:26,212 --> 00:02:28,442
- There's a bomb in there!
- No, there's not.

27
00:02:28,532 --> 00:02:30,170
- There's a bomb in there!
- There is not!

28
00:02:30,252 --> 00:02:31,401
There's a bomb in there!

29
00:02:31,492 --> 00:02:33,084
- You know how I know?
- How?

30
00:02:33,172 --> 00:02:36,289
I've got eight days till retirement
and I won't make a stupid mistake.

31
00:02:36,372 --> 00:02:39,364
There is no bomb!
I'll bet vital parts of my anatomy!

32
00:02:39,532 --> 00:02:40,681
RIGGS: Look.

33
00:02:41,732 --> 00:02:43,006
Trust me. Okay?

34
00:02:47,372 --> 00:02:49,522
That's usually my first mistake.

35
00:02:50,212 --> 00:02:51,361
Hey, Riggs!

36
00:02:51,452 --> 00:02:53,363
ROGER: Hey, wait. I'm coming.

37
00:02:53,532 --> 00:02:54,647
RIGGS: Rog?

38
00:02:54,812 --> 00:02:57,610
RIGGS: Is your insurance paid up?
ROGER: Of course. Why?

39
00:02:57,692 --> 00:03:00,650
RIGGS: There could be a bomb in here.
ROGER: Oh, God!

40
00:03:02,972 --> 00:03:06,442
ROGER: I hate it when I'm right.
RIGGS: Learn to trust your instincts more.

41
00:03:06,532 --> 00:03:07,760
ROGER: Oh, God.

42
00:03:08,412 --> 00:03:11,131
The first impression
can often be the right one.

43
00:03:13,252 --> 00:03:15,766
RIGGS: Drive shaft...
I wonder if there's a bomb.

44
00:03:15,852 --> 00:03:17,604
Just don't touch it.

45
00:03:18,892 --> 00:03:20,245
Just looking.

46
00:03:21,652 --> 00:03:24,405
[Riggs mutters to himself, bomb beeping]

47
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:28,489
What are you doing?
Don't open the door! Don't!

48
00:03:30,612 --> 00:03:32,284
[Doorhandle clicks]

49
00:03:32,892 --> 00:03:34,883
Son of a bitch, just look at it.

50
00:03:34,972 --> 00:03:36,883
That's all I'll do, just look.

51
00:03:39,852 --> 00:03:42,002
There's more plastic than Cher.

52
00:03:42,412 --> 00:03:44,448
RIGGS: I love this job.
This is amateur night.

53
00:03:44,532 --> 00:03:46,011
Open the door. I can't hear you.

54
00:03:46,092 --> 00:03:47,605
RIGGS: Open the door.

55
00:03:47,932 --> 00:03:49,285
Don't do nothing.

56
00:03:50,492 --> 00:03:51,925
Not that one!

57
00:03:52,172 --> 00:03:53,525
ROGER: You son of a bitch.

58
00:03:53,612 --> 00:03:56,524
RIGGS: This is a pretty shonky job.
I can dismantle it.

59
00:03:56,612 --> 00:03:59,001
It looks like Beirut to me. Let's go!

60
00:03:59,212 --> 00:04:00,167
[Thud]

61
00:04:00,412 --> 00:04:01,845
[Roger gasps]

62
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:05,928
Everybody's outside. Just me, you
and the cat are dumb enough to be here.

63
00:04:06,012 --> 00:04:08,162
Nearly a cat-tastrophe, huh?

64
00:04:09,292 --> 00:04:11,123
- Relax, Rog. Relax.
- Right.

65
00:04:11,212 --> 00:04:12,008
Don't do nothing.

66
00:04:12,092 --> 00:04:15,562
We've got 9 minutes and 7 seconds left.
You know what we can do?

67
00:04:15,852 --> 00:04:17,046
We could drive it out.

68
00:04:17,132 --> 00:04:18,645
Fine, it's your turn to drive.

69
00:04:18,732 --> 00:04:20,609
No keys. I could hot-wire it.

70
00:04:21,452 --> 00:04:23,761
Don't even say "hot-wire"
around this stuff!

71
00:04:23,852 --> 00:04:24,807
You're right.

72
00:04:24,892 --> 00:04:26,723
Why am I doing this? Why?

73
00:04:27,012 --> 00:04:29,731
I'm going to have to do it
the old-fashioned way.

74
00:04:29,892 --> 00:04:31,450
What are you thinking?

75
00:04:31,692 --> 00:04:33,569
ROGER: What are you thinking?

76
00:04:34,492 --> 00:04:36,687
- I'm thinking we should cut the blue wire.
- Wait!

77
00:04:36,772 --> 00:04:38,649
- That's not what I think.
- You think maybe the red?

78
00:04:38,732 --> 00:04:39,960
No! No!

79
00:04:40,132 --> 00:04:42,726
I'm thinking it's 8 minutes and 42 seconds.

80
00:04:42,852 --> 00:04:46,128
We can go upstairs, wait for
the bomb squad, and have a cappuccino.

81
00:04:46,212 --> 00:04:49,807
The bomb squad never gets here on time.
And it's 8 minutes, 31 seconds.

82
00:04:49,892 --> 00:04:51,086
Rog, please.

83
00:04:51,292 --> 00:04:52,202
Forget the cappuccino.

84
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:55,489
- You know what they'll say?
- "Get the fuck out of here!"

85
00:04:55,732 --> 00:04:59,725
But then they'll say: "Let's cut
the blue wire," which I'll do right now.

86
00:05:00,012 --> 00:05:01,684
- Wait, wait!
- What?

87
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:03,201
How can you be so sure?

88
00:05:03,292 --> 00:05:04,327
It's just a hunch.

89
00:05:04,412 --> 00:05:05,447
A hunch?

90
00:05:05,532 --> 00:05:06,931
Remember the bomb under your toilet?

91
00:05:07,012 --> 00:05:09,810
- How could I forget?
- Red wire, blue wire, same thing.

92
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:12,884
This is more simplified,
but a bit more powerful.

93
00:05:13,052 --> 00:05:14,883
From where I sat, I couldn't see.

94
00:05:14,972 --> 00:05:16,371
Forget it. Come on, trust me.

95
00:05:16,452 --> 00:05:17,680
Trust you?

96
00:05:17,852 --> 00:05:20,366
Guess not. I'm cutting the red wire, okay?

97
00:05:20,452 --> 00:05:21,805
Ho... ho...

98
00:05:22,972 --> 00:05:24,087
What? What?

99
00:05:24,172 --> 00:05:26,208
A minute ago you said blue!

100
00:05:27,132 --> 00:05:28,008
I did?

101
00:05:28,092 --> 00:05:29,241
You said blue!

102
00:05:29,812 --> 00:05:31,291
- I meant red.
- Sure?

103
00:05:31,612 --> 00:05:33,125
We can do it your way.

104
00:05:33,212 --> 00:05:35,362
ROGER: [Yells] My way? I don't have...
RIGGS: [Whispers] Quiet!

105
00:05:35,452 --> 00:05:36,487
I'm sure, okay?

106
00:05:36,572 --> 00:05:37,846
Ah, shit!

107
00:05:40,612 --> 00:05:41,806
RIGGS: Ready?

108
00:05:42,532 --> 00:05:43,248
Rog?

109
00:05:43,332 --> 00:05:44,242
What?

110
00:05:44,732 --> 00:05:47,610
Won't you miss all this good stuff
when you retire?

111
00:05:47,812 --> 00:05:50,087
RIGGS: Won't you miss it a little bit?

112
00:05:50,412 --> 00:05:51,731
[Riggs chuckles]

113
00:05:52,612 --> 00:05:54,443
RIGGS: I'm cutting the wire.

114
00:05:54,532 --> 00:05:56,409
RIGGS: Snip. All done.

115
00:05:58,172 --> 00:06:00,208
RIGGS: Rog...
ROGER: Yeah?

116
00:06:01,212 --> 00:06:02,247
Grab the cat!

117
00:06:02,332 --> 00:06:03,606
Grab the cat?

118
00:06:03,692 --> 00:06:05,922
RIGGS: Get out of there! Take cover!

119
00:06:06,892 --> 00:06:08,723
[Thunderous explosion]

120
00:06:10,652 --> 00:06:12,643
[Riggs and Roger yelling]

121
00:06:26,492 --> 00:06:28,687
[Glass and debris shattering]

122
00:06:41,772 --> 00:06:44,047
[Low rumbling turns to silence]

123
00:06:59,412 --> 00:07:01,209
[Both groan and sigh]

124
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:05,611
COP: Where are they?

125
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:08,405
[Cat meows]

126
00:07:10,572 --> 00:07:11,527
Bravo.

127
00:07:11,612 --> 00:07:13,204
[Sirens blaring]

128
00:07:16,612 --> 00:07:17,567
Whoops.

129
00:07:19,452 --> 00:07:20,965
Right. Whoops.

130
00:07:23,492 --> 00:07:24,641
Right.

131
00:07:28,052 --> 00:07:28,928
[Cat meows]

132
00:07:30,212 --> 00:07:33,124
ROGER: Seven days till retirement,
I'm busted down to patrolman.

133
00:07:33,212 --> 00:07:35,089
I should've cut the red wire.

134
00:07:35,572 --> 00:07:37,802
- You did.
- No, I cut the blue wire.

135
00:07:37,892 --> 00:07:39,484
That's what I meant.

136
00:07:39,652 --> 00:07:42,689
- We should've waited for the bomb squad.
- Must I hear this every day?

137
00:07:42,772 --> 00:07:45,809
- Every day until I retire!
- That'll be a week too long.

138
00:07:46,852 --> 00:07:49,002
- My feet are killing me.
- They're killing me, too.

139
00:07:49,092 --> 00:07:51,481
- How?
- I have to listen to you bitch about them!

140
00:07:51,572 --> 00:07:55,087
- Because you should've cut the red wire!
- I did cut the red wire!

141
00:07:56,332 --> 00:07:57,287
What's this?

142
00:07:57,372 --> 00:07:59,249
It's kind of soft... not a bulletproof vest.

143
00:07:59,332 --> 00:08:00,606
It won't keep anything out.

144
00:08:00,692 --> 00:08:02,444
It'll keep my stomach in.

145
00:08:02,532 --> 00:08:04,363
What've you got under there?

146
00:08:05,012 --> 00:08:06,206
It's a girdle.

147
00:08:06,452 --> 00:08:07,407
What?

148
00:08:08,692 --> 00:08:09,841
It's a girdle!

149
00:08:10,612 --> 00:08:11,647
Does Trish know?

150
00:08:11,732 --> 00:08:13,848
It's not a woman's girdle.
It's a man's girdle!

151
00:08:13,932 --> 00:08:16,048
- They make girdles for men?
- Yeah!

152
00:08:16,132 --> 00:08:17,485
- They do?
- Yeah, they do!

153
00:08:17,572 --> 00:08:19,244
I haven't worn this uniform in 15 years!

154
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:22,529
- Cleaners must have shrunk it.
- You should take it to Chin.

155
00:08:22,612 --> 00:08:26,287
ROGER: I did take it to Chin. Look at it.
It shrunk all up in here.

156
00:08:26,452 --> 00:08:28,044
ROGER: I have to hold my breath.

157
00:08:28,132 --> 00:08:29,247
Did you see that?

158
00:08:29,332 --> 00:08:31,402
ROGER: See what?
RIGGS: Jaywalker.

159
00:08:32,132 --> 00:08:33,247
Jaywalking?

160
00:08:33,892 --> 00:08:35,962
Hold it right there, pal.
Step up here, please.

161
00:08:36,052 --> 00:08:37,326
- Me?
- Yes, you.

162
00:08:37,492 --> 00:08:38,971
- What'd I do?
- Stand there.

163
00:08:39,052 --> 00:08:41,885
Jaywalking. I saw you.
I'll have to cite you.

164
00:08:41,972 --> 00:08:44,281
Jaywalking? Oh, Jesus, come on!

165
00:08:44,572 --> 00:08:46,244
ROGER: Should I radio for backup?

166
00:08:46,332 --> 00:08:48,402
RIGGS: Smart-ass.
Can you get the ticket book?

167
00:08:48,492 --> 00:08:50,403
You're hassling me for...

168
00:08:50,492 --> 00:08:52,244
RIGGS: Shut up!
ROGER: Yeah!

169
00:08:55,252 --> 00:08:58,528
- Do you know how to fill one of these out?
- A long time ago.

170
00:08:58,932 --> 00:09:02,527
ROGER: I can't read it.
The print is too small without my glasses.

171
00:09:02,732 --> 00:09:05,883
Can we speed this up?
You may have nothing to do, but I do.

172
00:09:05,972 --> 00:09:08,361
No, we can't, so will you shut up?

173
00:09:09,092 --> 00:09:11,083
RIGGS: Jaywalking.
ROGER: Ask for his license.

174
00:09:11,172 --> 00:09:12,924
RIGGS: License, for jaywalking?
ROGER: Yeah.

175
00:09:13,012 --> 00:09:15,810
I don't have it on me. I wasn't driving.

176
00:09:15,892 --> 00:09:18,486
I was walking.
Do I need a walking license now?

177
00:09:18,612 --> 00:09:20,443
RIGGS: Let's just shoot him!
JAYWALKER: Is he crazy?

178
00:09:20,532 --> 00:09:23,365
I'm going to drill him!
We'll make it look like suicide!

179
00:09:23,452 --> 00:09:26,205
RIGGS: Get out of the way!
ROGER: No, the video cameras!

180
00:09:26,292 --> 00:09:28,044
I don't care! I'll drill him!

181
00:09:28,132 --> 00:09:29,690
Get out of here, before he kills you!

182
00:09:29,772 --> 00:09:32,605
ROGER: Go that way! Not that way!
RIGGS: This way! Over here!

183
00:09:32,692 --> 00:09:33,681
RIGGS: Run!
ROGER: Now!

184
00:09:33,772 --> 00:09:35,091
BOTH: Run!

185
00:09:37,212 --> 00:09:38,611
[Both laugh]

186
00:09:45,492 --> 00:09:46,925
MAN: Wait a minute!

187
00:09:47,172 --> 00:09:48,890
You forgot to sign!

188
00:09:51,212 --> 00:09:52,406
What was that?

189
00:09:52,932 --> 00:09:55,651
MAN: Wait a minute.
You forgot to sign the form.

190
00:09:55,852 --> 00:09:56,841
Who're you?

191
00:09:56,932 --> 00:09:58,331
MAN: You're not the regular guy?

192
00:09:58,412 --> 00:10:00,846
COURIER: He's on vacation.
MAN: On vacation?

193
00:10:00,932 --> 00:10:02,684
Well, who the hell is that?

194
00:10:03,332 --> 00:10:04,731
Get in the truck!

195
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:06,086
[Gunshot]

196
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:08,569
[Scattered screaming]

197
00:10:12,132 --> 00:10:13,884
COURIER: You fucking prick!

198
00:10:14,612 --> 00:10:16,125
[Tires screech]

199
00:10:17,852 --> 00:10:19,285
ROGER: Riggs!

200
00:10:21,092 --> 00:10:22,571
DELORES: Are you a cop?

201
00:10:22,652 --> 00:10:25,644
Fourteen-sixty. Into pursuit.
Will continue transmission.

202
00:10:25,732 --> 00:10:26,767
GUARD: Call 911.

203
00:10:26,852 --> 00:10:29,650
Okay, honey. Let me drive.
We're in pursuit.

204
00:10:29,972 --> 00:10:32,088
DELORES: I'm driving! Don't worry.

205
00:10:32,852 --> 00:10:34,251
[Tires screech]

206
00:10:34,332 --> 00:10:36,323
[Grunting, struggling sounds]

207
00:10:38,412 --> 00:10:41,484
DELORES: This fool picked the wrong time
to mess with the wrong lady.

208
00:10:41,572 --> 00:10:43,005
Just stay close!

209
00:10:44,732 --> 00:10:46,006
[Man groans]

210
00:10:47,572 --> 00:10:48,721
[Bang]

211
00:10:49,212 --> 00:10:50,850
Right behind you, baby!

212
00:10:51,292 --> 00:10:52,566
DELORES: Take a good look!

213
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:55,610
Delores the Road Warrior
is dead on your raggedy ass!

214
00:10:57,932 --> 00:10:59,445
[Tires screech]

215
00:11:00,692 --> 00:11:02,728
[Truck engine accelerates]

216
00:11:03,972 --> 00:11:05,121
ROGER: Ram him!

217
00:11:05,212 --> 00:11:07,168
[Tires screech, car horns blare]

218
00:11:11,572 --> 00:11:13,324
- Watch out, Riggs!
- Come on!

219
00:11:16,372 --> 00:11:17,202
[Screams]

220
00:11:17,292 --> 00:11:18,441
[Bang]

221
00:11:21,892 --> 00:11:22,927
Are you married, sugar?

222
00:11:23,012 --> 00:11:25,321
What? Yes, 24 years! 24 years!

223
00:11:25,572 --> 00:11:27,164
Yeah, but is it working?

224
00:11:30,092 --> 00:11:31,684
[Car horn wails]

225
00:11:32,292 --> 00:11:35,090
- You can't get closer?
- I am! I'm getting closer.

226
00:11:37,532 --> 00:11:38,442
Hold on, Riggs!

227
00:11:38,532 --> 00:11:39,760
ROGER: Hold on!

228
00:11:48,492 --> 00:11:50,369
Hold on! Hold on! We got you!

229
00:11:50,452 --> 00:11:51,805
DELORES: Hold on!

230
00:11:52,652 --> 00:11:54,688
DELORES: I told you I could!
ROGER: Closer!

231
00:11:54,772 --> 00:11:56,649
RIGGS: Get me up there!
ROGER: Go!

232
00:11:56,732 --> 00:11:57,847
I am! I am!

233
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:03,961
ROGER: Back off!

234
00:12:04,052 --> 00:12:05,963
[Delores screams, loud thud]

235
00:12:09,532 --> 00:12:11,523
[Car screeches to a halt]

236
00:12:16,012 --> 00:12:17,286
If he falls, don't hit him!

237
00:12:17,372 --> 00:12:19,761
Don't worry, I've got something for you!

238
00:12:21,772 --> 00:12:23,967
[Sings with a powerful voice]

239
00:12:29,332 --> 00:12:31,129
[Continues bellowing]

240
00:12:33,492 --> 00:12:34,641
[Bang]

241
00:12:37,732 --> 00:12:39,404
[Car horns blaring]

242
00:12:39,692 --> 00:12:41,091
[Tires screeching]

243
00:12:47,252 --> 00:12:48,446
[Smack]

244
00:12:53,172 --> 00:12:54,844
[Tires screeching]

245
00:12:56,732 --> 00:12:59,804
Thanks for the interest, sugar,
but one thing at a time!

246
00:13:01,812 --> 00:13:03,768
[Driver screams in pain]

247
00:13:10,572 --> 00:13:12,244
[Truck horn wails]

248
00:13:13,612 --> 00:13:15,762
ROGER: Catch him!
DELORES: All right!

249
00:13:16,172 --> 00:13:17,446
[Gunshot]

250
00:13:17,732 --> 00:13:20,007
ROGER: Keep singing! Just stay close!

251
00:13:21,372 --> 00:13:22,885
[Driver groans]

252
00:13:26,932 --> 00:13:28,570
DELORES: Relax, baby. Relax.

253
00:13:28,652 --> 00:13:30,688
ROGER: Keep your hands off my thighs!

254
00:13:30,772 --> 00:13:33,809
ROGER: He's in trouble. Watch out!
DELORES: I got him!

255
00:13:39,052 --> 00:13:40,451
[Screeching]

256
00:13:45,652 --> 00:13:47,210
I'm getting too old for this.

257
00:13:47,292 --> 00:13:49,203
Not for me, you're not, sugar.

258
00:13:52,532 --> 00:13:54,921
You have the right to remain unconscious.

259
00:13:55,412 --> 00:13:57,607
Anything you say ain't gonna be much.

260
00:13:57,692 --> 00:13:59,364
[Truck horn honks]

261
00:14:01,972 --> 00:14:03,530
Hey, Riggs. Are you all right?

262
00:14:03,612 --> 00:14:07,651
I'm okay. I guess we'll have to book
this guy for not wearing his seat belt.

263
00:14:07,732 --> 00:14:09,609
That was dynamite driving.

264
00:14:09,692 --> 00:14:13,162
ROGER: She's a dynamite driver!
DELORES: I'll show you dynamite!

265
00:14:13,812 --> 00:14:15,131
Sho 'nuff!

266
00:14:16,532 --> 00:14:18,443
What have you two been up to?

267
00:14:18,652 --> 00:14:20,051
What do you mean? We were in pursuit!

268
00:14:20,132 --> 00:14:22,521
RIGGS: I saw you kiss her.
ROGER: She kissed me!

269
00:14:22,612 --> 00:14:25,604
It looked mutual to me.
Wipe that lipstick off.

270
00:14:25,692 --> 00:14:27,444
Hey, go spit, Riggs!

271
00:14:29,492 --> 00:14:30,686
Are you okay?

272
00:14:30,772 --> 00:14:32,171
Are you all right?

273
00:14:32,452 --> 00:14:33,646
Back to bed. Back to bed.

274
00:14:34,652 --> 00:14:36,722
Good morning, guys. Daddy.

275
00:14:37,092 --> 00:14:39,925
How about treating your dad
to breakfast today?

276
00:14:40,972 --> 00:14:44,408
CARRIE: You've got six more days to go.
RIGGS: Laundry service.

277
00:14:45,492 --> 00:14:46,925
TRISH: Hold this. Hangers?

278
00:14:47,012 --> 00:14:50,288
I'm springing for the soap.
Nothing too fancy. Cute dog.

279
00:14:50,452 --> 00:14:52,010
CARRIE: It's a Westie.

280
00:14:52,172 --> 00:14:53,446
'Morning, Trish.

281
00:14:54,012 --> 00:14:55,206
'Morning, Rog.

282
00:14:56,252 --> 00:14:57,526
RIGGS: Good morning, Nick.
NICK: Spare me.

283
00:14:57,612 --> 00:15:00,410
RIGGS: What, you didn't brush your teeth?
TRISH: Hold it, mister!

284
00:15:00,492 --> 00:15:02,244
Just looking for some orange juice.

285
00:15:02,332 --> 00:15:05,688
Don't get any fingerprints on the door
and put the glass in the dishwasher.

286
00:15:05,772 --> 00:15:07,364
Did somebody commit a murder?

287
00:15:07,452 --> 00:15:09,488
Someone's coming to see the house.

288
00:15:09,612 --> 00:15:12,251
RIGGS: I think a little mess
adds to the charm.

289
00:15:12,652 --> 00:15:14,131
[Tires squeal]

290
00:15:19,492 --> 00:15:21,403
[Dog barks in distance]

291
00:15:21,692 --> 00:15:23,125
LEO: How's this?

292
00:15:23,612 --> 00:15:25,409
LEO: Isn't this great? Okay? Okay?

293
00:15:25,492 --> 00:15:26,561
[Phone rings]

294
00:15:26,652 --> 00:15:28,005
Kelly's Pool Hall.

295
00:15:28,092 --> 00:15:30,765
Right, Kelly, hi. Let me speak to Dad.

296
00:15:31,052 --> 00:15:34,886
RIGGS: Hi, honey. How are you?
I thought I asked you not to call me here.

297
00:15:34,972 --> 00:15:36,849
RIGGS: It's for you.
ROGER: Me?

298
00:15:39,372 --> 00:15:40,691
Who is it? Hello?

299
00:15:40,772 --> 00:15:44,287
<i>Hi. It's my first day at work. Are you</i>
<i>going to come by and wish me luck?</i>

300
00:15:44,372 --> 00:15:46,602
LEO: Beautiful, huh?
Come on, check it out.

301
00:15:46,692 --> 00:15:48,011
WOMAN: Beautiful lawn.

302
00:15:48,092 --> 00:15:49,366
LEO: It's great.

303
00:15:49,452 --> 00:15:51,602
See how quiet it is here? Listen.

304
00:15:51,852 --> 00:15:53,205
Isn't that great? Come on.

305
00:15:53,292 --> 00:15:55,362
MAN: It's quiet.
LEO: The inside's even better.

306
00:15:55,452 --> 00:15:59,081
TRISH: It's the people to look at the house.
ROGER: And our broker.

307
00:16:01,772 --> 00:16:03,444
LEO: Just want to make sure.

308
00:16:03,532 --> 00:16:06,251
I'll show you this room first.
It's my favorite.

309
00:16:07,932 --> 00:16:10,241
- Is that it? Does that say it all?
- It's very nice.

310
00:16:10,332 --> 00:16:12,243
I love that picture window.

311
00:16:13,772 --> 00:16:16,206
LEO: It's just been completely replaced.
MAN: Why?

312
00:16:16,292 --> 00:16:19,090
A drug dealer came through with his car
and crashed right in.

313
00:16:19,172 --> 00:16:20,890
Shot up the whole place.

314
00:16:21,092 --> 00:16:24,084
Son of a bitch!
I'm going to cut him off at the knees!

315
00:16:25,372 --> 00:16:28,682
It's true. It's true. True.
Okay, okay, anyway, look.

316
00:16:28,772 --> 00:16:31,081
LEO: Do you like the drapes?
Maybe she'll leave them.

317
00:16:31,172 --> 00:16:32,969
ROGER: I thought you quit.
RIGGS: I did.

318
00:16:33,052 --> 00:16:35,088
ROGER: You'll stink up the house.
Don't smoke.

319
00:16:35,172 --> 00:16:36,730
RIGGS: I'm itching to.

320
00:16:36,972 --> 00:16:38,087
ROGER: Here.

321
00:16:38,892 --> 00:16:40,166
Chew on these.

322
00:16:40,492 --> 00:16:44,371
LEO: I have to tell you this. It's the law.
It's called "full disclosure."

323
00:16:44,452 --> 00:16:47,330
Anything else you want to disclose
before we go on?

324
00:16:48,012 --> 00:16:51,402
Now that you mention it, the bathroom
has been completely remodeled...

325
00:16:51,492 --> 00:16:53,244
...due to unexpected bomb damage.

326
00:16:53,332 --> 00:16:54,811
LEO: Hey, come on. It's okay.

327
00:16:54,892 --> 00:16:56,325
Son of a bitch!

328
00:16:56,412 --> 00:16:59,165
RIGGS: Don't, don't.
You'll never sell the house.

329
00:17:03,772 --> 00:17:06,127
Okay, okay. We saw enough
of the kitchen.

330
00:17:06,212 --> 00:17:10,967
LEO: I'll show you the upstairs. Wait till
you see it. It's beautiful. You'll love it.

331
00:17:12,332 --> 00:17:13,845
[Tires screech]

332
00:17:15,052 --> 00:17:17,725
ROGER: They're gone. Leo Getz,
I'm going to kill him!

333
00:17:17,812 --> 00:17:20,167
Son of a bitch! I'm going to kill him!

334
00:17:20,252 --> 00:17:22,163
You have to let me, Riggs!

335
00:17:24,252 --> 00:17:25,970
They weren't going to buy it anyway!

336
00:17:26,052 --> 00:17:29,089
- You scared them away!
- They couldn't afford to buy it!

337
00:17:29,172 --> 00:17:31,128
- Oh, I see.
- Okay, relax.

338
00:17:31,692 --> 00:17:35,048
I had to tell them everything.
It's the law. "Full disclosure."

339
00:17:35,132 --> 00:17:38,283
LEO: You must have heard of it?
ROGER: I'm a cop! I'm the law!

340
00:17:38,372 --> 00:17:41,364
RIGGS: Get off me! What is it with you?
LEO: Hold it!

341
00:17:42,172 --> 00:17:43,241
Okay, okay.

342
00:17:43,332 --> 00:17:46,483
At least he didn't tell them
about the nail-gun incident.

343
00:17:47,612 --> 00:17:50,570
I forgot. Did you have a permit
when you built over the garage?

344
00:17:50,652 --> 00:17:51,767
Permit?

345
00:17:51,852 --> 00:17:54,286
Hold it! Leo's here. I'll take care of it.

346
00:17:54,372 --> 00:17:57,364
I'll make some calls.
We'll get some back-dated permits.

347
00:17:57,452 --> 00:17:59,920
LEO: Which phone can I use?
ROGER: Sunroom.

348
00:18:02,412 --> 00:18:05,051
ROGER: It must be easier than this.
LEO: Count on Leo Getz.

349
00:18:05,132 --> 00:18:08,249
You need less aggravation.
Come to work with me.

350
00:18:08,572 --> 00:18:10,688
Thank you, Leo! Son of a bitch!

351
00:18:10,892 --> 00:18:14,680
Stop fronting yourself. You know?
Swing with me and my crew.

352
00:18:15,412 --> 00:18:17,448
[Rap music playing in car]

353
00:18:19,772 --> 00:18:21,603
DARRYL: Forget school.

354
00:18:24,092 --> 00:18:25,889
Here comes your pops.

355
00:18:26,892 --> 00:18:29,167
NICK: Later.
DARRYL: All right, gotcha.

356
00:18:29,852 --> 00:18:31,365
NICK: Next time.

357
00:18:34,492 --> 00:18:37,245
NEIGHBOR: 'Morning, Rog.
ROGER: How're you doing?

358
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:39,720
Hey, Nick.

359
00:18:40,692 --> 00:18:42,364
- Wasn't that Darryl?
- Yeah.

360
00:18:42,812 --> 00:18:45,042
I haven't seen him around in a while.

361
00:18:45,572 --> 00:18:46,721
He dropped out of high school.

362
00:18:46,812 --> 00:18:49,042
Those are pretty gang colors he's wearing.

363
00:18:49,132 --> 00:18:50,406
Yeah, I know.

364
00:18:51,772 --> 00:18:52,921
Hey, Nick?

365
00:18:53,852 --> 00:18:54,887
Yeah, Dad?

366
00:18:55,052 --> 00:18:56,246
Be good.

367
00:18:56,892 --> 00:18:57,768
Word.

368
00:19:00,412 --> 00:19:01,606
"Word," Nick.

369
00:19:02,052 --> 00:19:03,167
Word.

370
00:19:06,252 --> 00:19:07,367
"Word," Riggs.

371
00:19:07,452 --> 00:19:08,726
"Word," Rog.

372
00:19:09,812 --> 00:19:11,211
ROGER: What are we talking about?
RIGGS: "Word."

373
00:19:11,292 --> 00:19:13,760
Four letters. Starts with a "W",
"O" in the middle, "D" at the end.

374
00:19:13,852 --> 00:19:15,604
ROGER: Oh, yeah, that word.

375
00:19:16,732 --> 00:19:17,926
ROGER: "Word."

376
00:19:30,292 --> 00:19:33,443
JACK: Tyrone, my man, how are you?
TYRONE: Jack, how's it going?

377
00:19:33,532 --> 00:19:35,966
JACK: Let's take a walk.
TYRONE: Wait here for me.

378
00:19:36,052 --> 00:19:39,010
JACK: Look around. This is my dream
and it's all coming true.

379
00:19:39,092 --> 00:19:43,165
TYRONE: You sank your money into this,
out here in the middle of the desert?

380
00:19:43,292 --> 00:19:45,681
JACK: Know why it'll be a gold mine?
TYRONE: Do tell.

381
00:19:45,772 --> 00:19:49,401
Because no one wants to live
next door to a menace like you.

382
00:19:49,492 --> 00:19:52,564
I came to do business,
not to be insulted by you.

383
00:19:52,732 --> 00:19:54,211
Relax, Tyrone.

384
00:19:54,492 --> 00:19:56,608
Like houses, friendships need
strong foundations.

385
00:19:56,692 --> 00:19:58,922
Smitty, come here. Come here.

386
00:20:01,932 --> 00:20:05,083
What's wrong with you?
Don't I pay you good and take care of you?

387
00:20:05,172 --> 00:20:08,323
- Sure you do.
- What about the stunt you and Billy pulled?

388
00:20:08,852 --> 00:20:09,921
It was a good plan. It worked.

389
00:20:10,012 --> 00:20:12,082
It worked? It didn't work.

390
00:20:12,212 --> 00:20:13,884
You got nailed, first time out.

391
00:20:13,972 --> 00:20:16,281
Nobody who works for me
goes into business for themselves.

392
00:20:16,372 --> 00:20:17,725
Do you understand me?

393
00:20:17,812 --> 00:20:20,121
See how that can jeopardize everything?
Right, Tyrone?

394
00:20:20,212 --> 00:20:21,565
TYRONE: Whatever.

395
00:20:21,892 --> 00:20:24,486
JACK: Especially trying to pop
an armored car.

396
00:20:24,612 --> 00:20:28,127
JACK: Okay, Billy got caught.
There's nothing I can do about that now.

397
00:20:28,212 --> 00:20:30,772
He'll have to face the music on his own.

398
00:20:30,892 --> 00:20:32,450
But you and me...

399
00:20:32,732 --> 00:20:34,085
...we're gonna start over.

400
00:20:34,172 --> 00:20:35,651
You know what I mean?

401
00:20:36,732 --> 00:20:38,643
SMITTY: Whatever you say, Jack.
JACK: Good.

402
00:20:38,732 --> 00:20:41,166
Glad you understand
what I'm talking about.

403
00:20:41,852 --> 00:20:43,365
[Smitty groans]

404
00:20:45,052 --> 00:20:46,531
[Cement gurgling]

405
00:20:47,052 --> 00:20:49,612
Now we've got a relationship
we can build on.

406
00:20:51,492 --> 00:20:54,529
- Employee problems. You know how it is?
- Yeah, right.

407
00:20:54,852 --> 00:20:57,366
You invest time and energy
into training somebody.

408
00:20:57,452 --> 00:21:00,842
Then, they get greedy and do something
stupid that jeopardizes everything.

409
00:21:00,932 --> 00:21:02,206
It's a bitch!

410
00:21:02,412 --> 00:21:04,607
Stick around. This is the good part.

411
00:21:04,692 --> 00:21:07,252
We can put our initials in there, yeah?

412
00:21:08,012 --> 00:21:09,365
TYRONE: Jesus Christ!

413
00:21:09,452 --> 00:21:10,726
[Cackles]

414
00:21:12,812 --> 00:21:15,406
RIGGS: Lankershim and Vineland.
Where are we going?

415
00:21:15,492 --> 00:21:19,121
ROGER: Right here. Rianne's got a
new job. I promised her I'd stop by.

416
00:21:19,212 --> 00:21:21,043
RIGGS: That's a good reason.

417
00:21:21,612 --> 00:21:23,887
ROGER: All right. Here we are.

418
00:21:30,052 --> 00:21:33,203
ROGER: You got any silver, any change?
RIGGS: We're cops.

419
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:36,602
That's right, we're cops. Not crooks.
I'll get change.

420
00:21:45,932 --> 00:21:48,002
MAN: Get down! All of you!

421
00:21:51,652 --> 00:21:52,926
Get down!

422
00:22:01,892 --> 00:22:03,371
Riggs! Riggs!

423
00:22:06,572 --> 00:22:08,085
[Rianne screams]

424
00:22:09,172 --> 00:22:10,207
How do you like that?

425
00:22:10,292 --> 00:22:12,647
What are you doing with a rubber gun?

426
00:22:12,812 --> 00:22:14,040
This is a film!

427
00:22:14,132 --> 00:22:17,124
Cut, cut, cut! Who the fuck is this lunatic?

428
00:22:17,332 --> 00:22:20,642
DIRECTOR: Get him off my set.
ACTOR: This isn't part of the story.

429
00:22:20,732 --> 00:22:22,450
DIRECTOR: Can we get a cop?

430
00:22:23,372 --> 00:22:26,523
Rianne, I'm so sorry.
I feel like a microbe right now.

431
00:22:26,692 --> 00:22:28,444
You really thought I was in trouble?

432
00:22:28,532 --> 00:22:29,487
RIGGS: I did.

433
00:22:29,572 --> 00:22:32,245
A real cop! Go sit in your fucking trailer!

434
00:22:32,332 --> 00:22:34,971
DIRECTOR: Are you a fucking idiot?
RIGGS: I apologize.

435
00:22:35,052 --> 00:22:37,885
He's a friend of mine, a policeman.
He thought I was in trouble.

436
00:22:37,972 --> 00:22:38,848
ROGER: We're both...

437
00:22:38,932 --> 00:22:40,285
He's a friend of yours?

438
00:22:40,372 --> 00:22:43,648
Let me tell you something: You're fired.
Have a nice day.

439
00:22:43,932 --> 00:22:45,923
Fired? Riggs, what'd you do?

440
00:22:46,492 --> 00:22:47,766
You're not fired.

441
00:22:47,852 --> 00:22:49,922
No, you're not. Just take it easy.

442
00:22:50,012 --> 00:22:52,367
RIGGS: You can't fire her
for something I did.

443
00:22:52,452 --> 00:22:54,602
I don't care whose mistake it was!
She's fired!

444
00:22:54,692 --> 00:22:56,125
RIGGS: I apologize to everyone.

445
00:22:56,212 --> 00:22:57,361
Don't push him!

446
00:22:57,452 --> 00:22:58,726
DIRECTOR: All of you, go!

447
00:22:58,812 --> 00:23:00,643
Just take it easy. Don't push him.

448
00:23:00,732 --> 00:23:03,804
DIRECTOR: Get off my set, all right?
What are you, deaf?

449
00:23:04,012 --> 00:23:05,331
Get off my set!

450
00:23:05,412 --> 00:23:07,403
On any normal day,
I'd smack you in the mouth.

451
00:23:07,492 --> 00:23:08,447
Is that so?

452
00:23:08,532 --> 00:23:09,328
Don't!

453
00:23:09,412 --> 00:23:11,084
It's a normal day.

454
00:23:11,332 --> 00:23:14,085
I'm sorry. Listen, are you okay? I'm sorry.

455
00:23:14,172 --> 00:23:17,209
RIGGS: I'm all thumbs! He fell down!
Let me help you.

456
00:23:17,492 --> 00:23:19,164
I said, don't hit him!

457
00:23:19,252 --> 00:23:20,844
RIGGS: Is she fired?
DIRECTOR: Yes, she's fired!

458
00:23:20,932 --> 00:23:22,604
RIGGS: Is she fired?
DIRECTOR: No, no.

459
00:23:22,692 --> 00:23:23,886
ROGER: It's okay.
RIGGS: Does she get a raise?

460
00:23:23,972 --> 00:23:26,440
DIRECTOR: Yes! I said, "yes"!
RIGGS: Good.

461
00:23:26,532 --> 00:23:29,330
RIGGS: Rianne, I think you have
a new friend here.

462
00:23:30,252 --> 00:23:32,129
We'd like you to come back.

463
00:23:32,212 --> 00:23:34,487
[Applause and cheers from crew]

464
00:23:36,452 --> 00:23:39,012
ROGER: You can't settle every problem
with your fists.

465
00:23:39,092 --> 00:23:41,890
- I couldn't use my gun with that crowd.
- Six more days.

466
00:23:41,972 --> 00:23:43,690
Look, I don't want to hear that.

467
00:23:43,772 --> 00:23:46,491
Did Rianne get her job back?
Did she get a raise?

468
00:23:46,572 --> 00:23:48,324
I don't hear a "thank you."

469
00:23:48,612 --> 00:23:51,922
Maybe I should become a Hollywood agent.
What do you think?

470
00:23:52,732 --> 00:23:54,529
ROGER: It won't work.
RIGGS: Why?

471
00:23:54,612 --> 00:23:56,842
ROGER: You don't have that killer instinct.

472
00:23:56,932 --> 00:23:58,445
RIGGS: Son of a bitch!

473
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:02,851
- We should've put a bag on the meter.
- I'll put it in the glove compartment.

474
00:24:02,972 --> 00:24:04,291
I don't do that anymore.

475
00:24:04,372 --> 00:24:05,930
Oh, yeah? Good man.

476
00:24:06,012 --> 00:24:08,162
It's full. Put it in the back seat.

477
00:24:11,932 --> 00:24:14,890
- You really like those things?
- These? They're good.

478
00:24:14,972 --> 00:24:16,564
[Roger chuckles]

479
00:24:17,532 --> 00:24:20,729
You can eat a box of them
and still be dying for a cigarette.

480
00:24:20,812 --> 00:24:22,404
[Roger chuckles]

481
00:24:24,012 --> 00:24:26,287
- Did you cut yourself shaving?
- Yeah.

482
00:24:27,052 --> 00:24:28,405
RIGGS: Old razor?

483
00:24:28,932 --> 00:24:30,081
Old face.

484
00:24:32,092 --> 00:24:35,050
You're letting this retirement thing
get you down.

485
00:24:35,892 --> 00:24:38,725
Spend a few more years
to get used to the idea. Why quit?

486
00:24:38,812 --> 00:24:41,610
- I've got plans for my retirement.
- Oh, yeah, plans.

487
00:24:41,692 --> 00:24:43,205
- I do. Big plans.
- Big plans?

488
00:24:43,292 --> 00:24:45,248
- I've had them for a long time.
- Like what?

489
00:24:45,332 --> 00:24:46,560
Like...

490
00:24:48,292 --> 00:24:50,089
- Things, man!
- Things!

491
00:24:50,732 --> 00:24:51,687
Things!

492
00:24:51,772 --> 00:24:53,251
Things that I've put off.

493
00:24:53,332 --> 00:24:55,926
Oh, those things. I've got those, too.

494
00:24:56,492 --> 00:24:58,926
I see you've given this a lot of thought.

495
00:24:59,852 --> 00:25:01,285
[Roger sighs]

496
00:25:01,532 --> 00:25:02,647
Yeah.

497
00:25:03,412 --> 00:25:05,368
I've given it a lot of thought.

498
00:25:17,772 --> 00:25:18,841
[Gunshot]

499
00:25:21,132 --> 00:25:22,485
[Deep sigh]

500
00:25:23,852 --> 00:25:25,444
RIGGS: [Yells] Goddamn it!

501
00:25:25,532 --> 00:25:28,604
COP: What's going on?
RIGGS: I'm pissed off. You need a reason?

502
00:25:28,692 --> 00:25:30,284
COP: I thought I heard gunfire.

503
00:25:30,372 --> 00:25:32,567
RIGGS: Get your hearing checked!
Put that away!

504
00:25:32,652 --> 00:25:33,880
What're you looking at?

505
00:25:33,972 --> 00:25:35,530
Hey, man. Peace.

506
00:25:53,852 --> 00:25:55,763
[Thunderous gun blasts]

507
00:25:56,892 --> 00:25:58,962
COP 1: Why'd you call us down here?

508
00:26:01,332 --> 00:26:02,606
RIGGS: How're you doing, son?

509
00:26:02,692 --> 00:26:05,081
RIGGS: Does your mother
know you're here?

510
00:26:08,252 --> 00:26:10,368
RIGGS: Did you do this?
COP 2: Nice shooting.

511
00:26:10,452 --> 00:26:12,329
Better than Billy the Kid.

512
00:26:12,612 --> 00:26:14,489
Diaper rash makes you cranky.

513
00:26:14,612 --> 00:26:17,763
Give it to your mom.
Maybe she'll stick it on the refrigerator.

514
00:26:17,852 --> 00:26:19,922
- Can I borrow your glasses?
- Yeah.

515
00:26:20,132 --> 00:26:21,531
RIGGS: Who's wearing?

516
00:26:21,612 --> 00:26:22,931
Roger, you are.

517
00:26:23,012 --> 00:26:24,889
Why me? You guys should be wearing.

518
00:26:24,972 --> 00:26:27,008
SQUAD MEMBER:
Mr. Murtaugh, let me assist you.

519
00:26:27,092 --> 00:26:29,367
I don't need help.
I've been dressing myself since I was 30.

520
00:26:29,452 --> 00:26:31,727
- Okay, man, just trying to help.
- Get back.

521
00:26:31,812 --> 00:26:33,404
All you perverts, turn your heads.

522
00:26:33,492 --> 00:26:36,245
COP 3: Take it off, baby!
ROGER: Hold this shirt.

523
00:26:37,212 --> 00:26:39,043
SQUAD MEMBER: You're wearing a girdle!

524
00:26:39,132 --> 00:26:41,202
- He's got a girdle!
- This is not a girdle.

525
00:26:41,292 --> 00:26:43,408
ROGER: This is not a girdle. It's my back!

526
00:26:43,492 --> 00:26:45,130
<i>My back went out on me.</i>

527
00:26:46,092 --> 00:26:49,971
I hurt my back this morning lifting weights.
What're you talking about?

528
00:26:50,092 --> 00:26:51,445
RIGGS: I saw him do it.

529
00:26:51,532 --> 00:26:52,567
Everybody, listen up.

530
00:26:52,652 --> 00:26:55,689
I want you all to look at
these... Iovely bullets.

531
00:26:55,852 --> 00:26:56,568
Cute.

532
00:26:56,652 --> 00:27:00,042
Notice the smooth jacket.
Pay particular attention to the tip.

533
00:27:04,572 --> 00:27:07,928
Now you've all seen these vests
stop a.357 magnum bullet.

534
00:27:08,012 --> 00:27:09,843
ALL: Yeah.
RIGGS: Okay.

535
00:27:12,212 --> 00:27:13,440
Observe.

536
00:27:15,012 --> 00:27:16,365
[Gun blast]

537
00:27:17,292 --> 00:27:18,964
[Gun chamber clicks]

538
00:27:19,052 --> 00:27:20,770
[Pulley mechanism hums]

539
00:27:27,852 --> 00:27:29,649
RIGGS: Son of a bitch!

540
00:27:31,212 --> 00:27:34,284
COP 1: Armor-piercing bullets?
RIGGS: Yeah, cop killers.

541
00:27:35,212 --> 00:27:38,682
Those bullets came from the gun
of a suspect we arrested yesterday.

542
00:27:38,772 --> 00:27:40,888
They're out there on the streets.

543
00:27:41,012 --> 00:27:44,084
Vests are optional, boys and girls.
Especially boys.

544
00:27:44,452 --> 00:27:45,726
See you, Riggs.

545
00:27:48,252 --> 00:27:49,731
ROGER: Cop killers.

546
00:27:51,612 --> 00:27:53,648
[Whispers] Son of a bitch.

547
00:27:55,732 --> 00:28:00,328
I think we should talk to Billy Phelps.
I'll have him brought in for interrogation.

548
00:28:08,252 --> 00:28:10,641
I'm here to talk to Billy Phelps.

549
00:28:10,852 --> 00:28:13,241
- Can I see your ID, please?
- Sure.

550
00:28:13,692 --> 00:28:17,048
William Phelps, armored car suspect.
He's been moved to Interrogation.

551
00:28:17,132 --> 00:28:20,329
- Do you know where that is?
- Sure. I've been there a lot.

552
00:28:29,092 --> 00:28:30,650
ROGER: Same floor.

553
00:28:32,012 --> 00:28:35,368
[Whispers] I guess now you're retiring,
that Swiss bank account...

554
00:28:35,452 --> 00:28:37,443
...will come in pretty handy.

555
00:28:37,532 --> 00:28:40,171
How much you got in there, a million?
Million and a half?

556
00:28:40,252 --> 00:28:42,004
ROGER: Five.
RIGGS: Five?

557
00:28:42,372 --> 00:28:44,124
Well, you deserve it.

558
00:28:44,292 --> 00:28:47,443
It's better than those
miserable drug dealers getting it.

559
00:28:51,052 --> 00:28:52,770
What're you talking about?

560
00:28:53,092 --> 00:28:56,721
Don't sweat it. You laundered it,
didn't you? They can't trace it.

561
00:28:57,052 --> 00:28:58,849
RIGGS: They can't trace it.
ROGER: What?

562
00:28:58,932 --> 00:29:02,129
So long as I get an invite
to <i>Casa de</i> Murtaugh, I'm happy.

563
00:29:02,212 --> 00:29:03,406
<i>Casa</i> what?

564
00:29:03,532 --> 00:29:05,488
- I've never been to Portugal.
- Stop joking.

565
00:29:05,572 --> 00:29:06,687
She's a cop!

566
00:29:06,772 --> 00:29:09,809
I know she's a cop.
She's probably on the take, too.

567
00:29:10,932 --> 00:29:12,570
The whole Force is bent.

568
00:29:12,892 --> 00:29:15,281
RIGGS: She may be wearing a skirt,
but we're all brothers.

569
00:29:15,372 --> 00:29:18,364
You know I have nothing.
I ain't been to Portugal.

570
00:29:19,052 --> 00:29:20,804
RIGGS: Listen to me.

571
00:29:23,932 --> 00:29:26,127
LORNA: [Whispers] Son of a bitch.

572
00:29:26,452 --> 00:29:28,363
OFFICER: How're you doing?
LORNA: Fine.

573
00:29:28,452 --> 00:29:31,444
OFFICER: Who is it today?
RIGGS & LORNA: Billy Phelps.

574
00:29:31,892 --> 00:29:32,927
Who're you?

575
00:29:33,012 --> 00:29:35,651
Fly me. I'm your friendly
Portuguese airline.

576
00:29:35,932 --> 00:29:37,411
She's Infernal Affairs, Rog.

577
00:29:37,492 --> 00:29:38,766
LORNA: How'd you know?

578
00:29:38,852 --> 00:29:41,650
I took the liberty
of looking at your file folder.

579
00:29:42,492 --> 00:29:43,641
Lorna Cole.

580
00:29:44,532 --> 00:29:47,285
- And you're Sergeant Murtaugh.
- I used to be.

581
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:50,205
What's Infernal Repairs
want with our collar?

582
00:29:50,492 --> 00:29:52,164
We're taking over, thanks.

583
00:29:52,252 --> 00:29:53,970
Nobody told us they were taking over.

584
00:29:54,052 --> 00:29:55,929
Nobody has to tell you anything,
Patrolman.

585
00:29:56,012 --> 00:29:57,365
I want to go and see the captain.

586
00:29:57,452 --> 00:30:00,171
You want to see the captain?
Let's go see the captain.

587
00:30:00,252 --> 00:30:03,289
LORNA: And put on a vest.
RIGGS: Oh, are you wearing one?

588
00:30:03,372 --> 00:30:05,363
ROGER: Just take it easy, man.

589
00:30:07,452 --> 00:30:09,204
[Riggs sighs deeply]

590
00:30:09,652 --> 00:30:10,971
[Elevator rings]

591
00:30:17,212 --> 00:30:20,284
Hey, guys. Phelps, William.
Actually, his name's Billy.

592
00:30:20,532 --> 00:30:21,806
OFFICER: You, too?

593
00:30:21,892 --> 00:30:23,883
OFFICER: Popular guy today.
JACK: Somebody with him?

594
00:30:23,972 --> 00:30:26,850
No, not really.
He's down the hall to the right.

595
00:30:27,012 --> 00:30:28,968
Want to sign in here, Sarge?

596
00:30:29,532 --> 00:30:30,647
RIGGS: Miss.

597
00:30:31,452 --> 00:30:33,204
RIGGS: What's Internal Affairs doing here?

598
00:30:33,292 --> 00:30:35,044
MURPHY: Don't start.
I just found out myself.

599
00:30:35,132 --> 00:30:37,168
This is Herman Walters,
Chief of Intelligence.

600
00:30:37,252 --> 00:30:39,243
You haven't met his daughter,
Lorna Doone.

601
00:30:39,332 --> 00:30:40,890
LORNA: Pleased to meet you.

602
00:30:40,972 --> 00:30:43,645
The Phelps case has been transferred
to Internal Affairs.

603
00:30:43,732 --> 00:30:44,562
RIGGS: Why?

604
00:30:44,652 --> 00:30:46,608
MURPHY: I can't tell you.
WALTERS: That's classified.

605
00:30:46,692 --> 00:30:49,206
We busted our buns busting this guy.
We busted him.

606
00:30:49,292 --> 00:30:51,408
Busted is right.
He spent the night in the hospital.

607
00:30:51,492 --> 00:30:53,528
ROGER: He didn't buckle up.
RIGGS: We even cited him.

608
00:30:53,612 --> 00:30:55,443
I know, I read your report.

609
00:30:55,612 --> 00:30:58,445
LORNA: Our cases have, unfortunately,
crossed paths here.

610
00:30:58,532 --> 00:31:00,887
That's all I can say.
We'll take over from here.

611
00:31:00,972 --> 00:31:03,202
Captain, what is she talking about here?

612
00:31:03,292 --> 00:31:05,886
WALTERS: That's classified.
ROGER: No, I'm talking to him.

613
00:31:05,972 --> 00:31:07,371
I'm telling you...

614
00:31:07,452 --> 00:31:09,807
No, I said, "Captain."
I'm talking to the captain.

615
00:31:09,892 --> 00:31:12,770
WALTERS: That's classified!
ROGER: I'm talking to him!

616
00:31:12,852 --> 00:31:15,082
RIGGS: That's bullshit!
MURPHY: Riggs!

617
00:31:16,452 --> 00:31:19,012
MURPHY: Maybe these guys can contribute
something to this case?

618
00:31:19,092 --> 00:31:22,289
From their records,
they only contribute mayhem and chaos.

619
00:31:22,452 --> 00:31:24,682
No, I'm Chaos, he's Mayhem.
We're a double act.

620
00:31:24,772 --> 00:31:26,603
What are we,
required reading or something?

621
00:31:26,692 --> 00:31:28,091
As a matter of fact, you are.

622
00:31:28,172 --> 00:31:31,164
It's a cross between <i>Police Gazette</i>
and <i>Mad</i> magazine.

623
00:31:31,252 --> 00:31:34,085
RIGGS: What's wrong with <i>Mad</i>?
LORNA: Nothing, I used to read it...

624
00:31:34,172 --> 00:31:35,685
You've got some taste.

625
00:31:35,772 --> 00:31:37,091
...when I was 12.

626
00:31:38,212 --> 00:31:39,725
Riggs, let's go.

627
00:31:39,812 --> 00:31:41,723
ROGER: We busted him,
we can talk to him.

628
00:31:41,812 --> 00:31:44,042
WALTERS: Captain.
MURPHY: Riggs. Murtaugh.

629
00:31:44,132 --> 00:31:46,202
MURPHY: Get your asses back here.

630
00:31:49,172 --> 00:31:50,844
You'll be needing these.

631
00:31:51,572 --> 00:31:53,483
I'm reinstating both of you.

632
00:31:53,972 --> 00:31:56,440
ROGER: Don't you just love him?
RIGGS: Yeah.

633
00:31:56,532 --> 00:31:57,647
ROGER: God!

634
00:31:59,572 --> 00:32:01,085
You really are a beautiful man.

635
00:32:01,172 --> 00:32:02,764
Just get rid of the blues.

636
00:32:02,852 --> 00:32:06,322
MURPHY: They don't go with your ponytail.
RIGGS: Absolutely not.

637
00:32:07,212 --> 00:32:08,361
RIGGS: Yeah, right.

638
00:32:08,452 --> 00:32:09,487
Get a haircut!

639
00:32:09,572 --> 00:32:10,687
Of course, I won't.

640
00:32:10,772 --> 00:32:12,842
WALTERS: You've exceeded your authority,
Captain.

641
00:32:12,932 --> 00:32:15,526
MURPHY: That's not how I see it.
WALTERS: That's how the chief will see it.

642
00:32:15,612 --> 00:32:17,489
- Take it up with him.
- I think I will.

643
00:32:17,572 --> 00:32:21,167
Catch up with them. We don't want this
screwed up with cowboy tactics.

644
00:32:21,252 --> 00:32:22,446
Son of a bitch.

645
00:32:24,772 --> 00:32:25,807
Hi, Billy.

646
00:32:28,772 --> 00:32:29,727
Jack!

647
00:32:29,812 --> 00:32:30,927
Bye, Billy.

648
00:32:31,012 --> 00:32:33,162
[Multiple silenced gunshots]

649
00:32:38,212 --> 00:32:39,725
See you, Billy.

650
00:32:46,212 --> 00:32:48,089
OFFICER: Sergeant,
did you get what you need?

651
00:32:48,172 --> 00:32:50,686
Not really. It's a dead issue, I'm afraid.

652
00:32:52,252 --> 00:32:54,288
RIGGS: How long has Phelps
been doing this?

653
00:32:54,372 --> 00:32:57,091
LORNA: Doing what?
RIGGS: This armored-car thing.

654
00:32:57,252 --> 00:33:00,164
I wouldn't know.
I'm not interested in armored cars.

655
00:33:12,972 --> 00:33:15,247
I don't think she's telling us everything.

656
00:33:15,332 --> 00:33:16,560
I think you're right.

657
00:33:16,652 --> 00:33:19,212
Boy, these six days are going to be rough.

658
00:33:19,292 --> 00:33:21,010
ROGER: God, be good to me.

659
00:33:23,252 --> 00:33:26,767
MURPHY: Shit, son of a bitch knew
there was a camera in the wall.

660
00:33:27,532 --> 00:33:28,169
Damn it!

661
00:33:28,252 --> 00:33:30,812
He didn't know there was one
in the interrogation room.

662
00:33:30,892 --> 00:33:32,291
ROGER: There isn't.

663
00:33:32,372 --> 00:33:34,363
LORNA: We installed them six months ago.

664
00:33:34,452 --> 00:33:36,522
LORNA: Every station.
MURPHY: That's great.

665
00:33:36,612 --> 00:33:38,967
Six months and we don't know about it?

666
00:33:39,052 --> 00:33:40,644
This is the "police police," Captain.

667
00:33:40,732 --> 00:33:44,088
"Police police." Very good. Can you say
that three times in a row, real fast?

668
00:33:44,172 --> 00:33:46,481
RIGGS: Why? Am I getting to you?
LORNA: Are you trying to bait me?

669
00:33:46,572 --> 00:33:47,925
I'm a master at it.

670
00:33:48,012 --> 00:33:49,206
That figures.

671
00:33:49,292 --> 00:33:51,886
Baiting master. Great, man,
try all the tricks.

672
00:33:51,972 --> 00:33:53,610
Freeze that. Stop it.

673
00:33:53,732 --> 00:33:55,211
MURPHY: Jack Travis.

674
00:33:55,292 --> 00:33:56,202
BOTH: Who?

675
00:33:56,292 --> 00:33:58,522
Lieutenant Jack Edward Travis.

676
00:33:58,972 --> 00:34:00,087
He was one of us.

677
00:34:00,172 --> 00:34:03,642
MURPHY: Hell of a brutal cop.
He could beat a confession out of anyone.

678
00:34:03,732 --> 00:34:04,608
A dirty cop.

679
00:34:04,692 --> 00:34:06,683
LORNA: I've never seen
so many suspensions...

680
00:34:06,772 --> 00:34:08,763
<i>... and reprimands and charges</i>
<i>of misconduct.</i>

681
00:34:08,852 --> 00:34:11,082
He's also as tough as they come.

682
00:34:11,612 --> 00:34:12,840
What happened to him?

683
00:34:12,932 --> 00:34:14,047
I don't know.

684
00:34:14,132 --> 00:34:17,727
His partner and him were on a stakeout.
He went for coffee, never came back.

685
00:34:17,812 --> 00:34:20,280
Looks like he's had
one cappuccino too many.

686
00:34:20,452 --> 00:34:22,170
We'd better brief Walters.

687
00:34:22,532 --> 00:34:24,602
LORNA: Excuse me, cute stuff.

688
00:34:24,772 --> 00:34:27,923
RIGGS: That's harassment.
ROGER: Cute stuff. That's you.

689
00:34:28,012 --> 00:34:31,368
RIGGS: Captain.
LORNA: Boys, boys. Just the captain.

690
00:34:31,492 --> 00:34:34,848
Your involvement in this case ended
when Phelps hit the floor.

691
00:34:35,012 --> 00:34:37,731
Why don't you just go back
and beat your street?

692
00:34:38,212 --> 00:34:41,010
LEO: Now's the time to buy.
MURPHY: Not now.

693
00:34:41,172 --> 00:34:43,163
- Hey, Roger, Roger!
- Not now, Leo!

694
00:34:43,252 --> 00:34:45,812
- Not now!
- We got to talk, babe, okay?

695
00:34:45,892 --> 00:34:47,723
You're in trouble. You've got termites.

696
00:34:47,812 --> 00:34:49,006
Termites?

697
00:34:49,332 --> 00:34:51,368
- Oh, God!
- You're infested!

698
00:34:52,132 --> 00:34:53,770
The only thing holding up your house
is the paint.

699
00:34:53,852 --> 00:34:54,921
We should go.

700
00:34:55,012 --> 00:34:57,162
Leo, could you get the place fumigated?

701
00:34:57,252 --> 00:34:59,561
We should pull every file on this guy.

702
00:34:59,652 --> 00:35:01,961
I know this guy.
Are you watching <i>Geraldo</i>?

703
00:35:02,052 --> 00:35:03,201
RIGGS: What?
LEO: I know the guy.

704
00:35:03,292 --> 00:35:05,931
RIGGS: How do you know him?
LEO: I've seen the guy before.

705
00:35:06,012 --> 00:35:08,207
ROGER: Where?
LEO: I don't know. I recognize him...

706
00:35:08,292 --> 00:35:10,886
His name is Jack Travis.
Does that ring a bell?

707
00:35:11,812 --> 00:35:13,689
Hands off the clothes. Okay?

708
00:35:14,052 --> 00:35:15,883
I'm thinking. Let me think.

709
00:35:16,612 --> 00:35:18,125
It was a big party.

710
00:35:18,212 --> 00:35:21,329
Someone brought a monkey
that knocked over the salad bar.

711
00:35:21,492 --> 00:35:24,609
And this guy comes in
and introduces me to another guy...

712
00:35:24,772 --> 00:35:26,524
...who wants a favor.

713
00:35:27,012 --> 00:35:28,684
- I got it! I got it!
- What?

714
00:35:28,892 --> 00:35:29,927
He's got it!

715
00:35:30,052 --> 00:35:31,770
- I remember!
- You remember!

716
00:35:32,132 --> 00:35:34,726
Don't do it. Don't let the earring fool you.

717
00:35:35,252 --> 00:35:37,447
- We're back. We're back!
- Yeah. Yeah.

718
00:35:37,532 --> 00:35:38,567
Listen, listen.

719
00:35:38,652 --> 00:35:40,210
Can I have a gun this time?

720
00:35:40,292 --> 00:35:41,725
[Echoing] No!

721
00:35:42,572 --> 00:35:44,642
[Crash, ambient game noise]

722
00:35:47,292 --> 00:35:49,567
[Scattered cheering, hollering]

723
00:35:50,492 --> 00:35:54,724
Okay, this is it! These guys always
wanted me to do favors for them!

724
00:35:55,372 --> 00:35:58,967
Like, some guys wanted broads,
another guy wanted Cuban cigars.

725
00:35:59,132 --> 00:36:00,770
Your guy, hockey!

726
