821
00:41:28,292 --> 00:41:29,281
LEO: Shit.

822
00:41:29,372 --> 00:41:30,964
RIGGS: Take it easy. Two days.

823
00:41:31,052 --> 00:41:33,247
DOCTOR: Two days and you'll be out.
No problem.

824
00:41:33,332 --> 00:41:34,401
LEO: I'll see you guys.

825
00:41:34,492 --> 00:41:36,210
RIGGS: We won't make a move
without you.

826
00:41:36,292 --> 00:41:37,884
I thought that bullet sounded different.

827
00:41:37,972 --> 00:41:40,122
DOCTOR: Relax.
They'll be there when you get out.

828
00:41:40,212 --> 00:41:41,201
LEO: I'm fine.

829
00:41:41,292 --> 00:41:43,248
LEO: You own your house, Doc?
DOCTOR: What?

830
00:41:43,332 --> 00:41:45,163
- You don't recognize my face?
- No, sir.

831
00:41:45,252 --> 00:41:45,923
Watch.

832
00:41:46,772 --> 00:41:50,367
RIGGS: It's about time. These doggy treats
are okay, but I need some human food.

833
00:41:50,452 --> 00:41:54,047
ROGER: Don't worry. I'll make you
the best thing you've ever had.

834
00:41:54,252 --> 00:41:55,651
RIGGS: Good.

835
00:41:56,172 --> 00:41:58,163
ROGER: You ever eat
one of my hamburgers?

836
00:41:58,252 --> 00:42:00,163
RIGGS: I've been lucky so far.

837
00:42:01,052 --> 00:42:02,451
ROGER: Fast Eddie!

838
00:42:02,812 --> 00:42:04,564
ROGER: How's business?
EDDIE: Booming. Can't you tell?

839
00:42:04,652 --> 00:42:07,041
ROGER: Yeah, I'm looking at it.
Did you meet my partner?

840
00:42:07,132 --> 00:42:09,805
I want to cook one
of those monster burgers for him.

841
00:42:09,892 --> 00:42:11,245
EDDIE: Go for it.
ROGER: All right.

842
00:42:11,332 --> 00:42:13,323
RIGGS: You'll let him cook?
EDDIE: Do I have a choice?

843
00:42:13,412 --> 00:42:15,607
ROGER: No, because it's Wednesday.

844
00:42:15,772 --> 00:42:17,285
RIGGS: He's too big to argue with.

845
00:42:17,372 --> 00:42:19,283
