886
00:44:21,012 --> 00:44:22,365
ROGER: All right, asshole!

887
00:44:22,452 --> 00:44:24,602
I want to see your hands, right now!

888
00:44:24,732 --> 00:44:26,450
[Multiple gunshots]

889
00:44:49,812 --> 00:44:51,165
Back me up, Riggs!

890
00:45:15,812 --> 00:45:17,086
ROGER: Darryl?

891
00:45:22,932 --> 00:45:24,206
Fuck, no!

892
00:45:24,572 --> 00:45:25,607
Fuck, no!

893
00:45:28,812 --> 00:45:31,849
Call an ambulance!
Call an ambulance! Breathe!

894
00:45:32,452 --> 00:45:34,090
ROGER: Please, breathe!

895
00:45:34,372 --> 00:45:35,566
<i>Breathe!</i>

896
00:45:35,732 --> 00:45:37,404
Call an ambulance!

897
00:45:38,532 --> 00:45:40,602
Come on! Breathe! Oh, God!

898
00:45:40,812 --> 00:45:42,325
Fuck, it's Darryl!

899
00:45:44,612 --> 00:45:46,204
Oh, God, don't do this to me! Breathe!

900
00:45:46,292 --> 00:45:48,760
RIGGS: He's dead.
ROGER: Breathe! Breathe!

901
00:45:48,852 --> 00:45:51,320
ROGER: God, don't do this!
RIGGS: He's dead.

902
00:45:51,412 --> 00:45:53,482
RIGGS: He's dead! Rog, he's dead!

903
00:45:53,772 --> 00:45:56,240
He's dead, Rog!
Don't mess with the corpse.

904
00:45:56,532 --> 00:45:59,490
He's dead. Come on, man,
it was a clean shoot.

905
00:45:59,732 --> 00:46:01,723
It's okay, it was a clean shoot.

906
00:46:01,812 --> 00:46:03,962
He was gonna do you
and he was gonna do me.

907
00:46:04,052 --> 00:46:05,724
It's okay. Are you okay?

908
00:46:06,332 --> 00:46:07,765
It's not okay.

909
00:46:09,012 --> 00:46:10,445
I know that kid.

910
00:46:13,092 --> 00:46:14,366
I know that kid.

911
00:46:15,692 --> 00:46:17,410
ROGER: He's Nick's friend.

912
00:46:32,892 --> 00:46:34,120
[Phone rings]

913
00:46:34,212 --> 00:46:36,521
NICK: I got it, Mom.
TRISH: I'll get it.

914
00:46:36,652 --> 00:46:37,721
Hello?

915
00:46:38,052 --> 00:46:39,326
Hi, Martin.

916
00:46:39,972 --> 00:46:41,246
He's not here.

917
00:46:48,532 --> 00:46:50,204
[Whispers] Oh, my God!

918
00:46:53,092 --> 00:46:54,286
Thanks.

919
00:47:05,812 --> 00:47:07,803
[Car screeches to a halt]

920
00:47:22,932 --> 00:47:23,967
Fuck!

921
00:47:27,452 --> 00:47:28,805
[Tires screech]

922
00:47:29,692 --> 00:47:31,808
RIGGS: How're you doing?
Taking your vitamins?

923
00:47:31,892 --> 00:47:35,202
MURPHY: Riggs, how's Murtaugh?
RIGGS: He's good. He's fine.

924
00:47:35,412 --> 00:47:38,290
- I'm sure he's anything but fine.
- Really, he's okay.

925
00:47:38,372 --> 00:47:41,762
- I'd really like to talk to him.
- That's not such a good idea.

926
00:47:42,332 --> 00:47:44,129
The best thing to do is to leave him alone.

927
00:47:44,212 --> 00:47:45,691
Let's get something for your cold.

928
00:47:45,772 --> 00:47:48,047
DOCTOR: I know what I'm talking about.

929
00:47:48,852 --> 00:47:51,764
LORNA: We have to talk.
RIGGS: Talking to you is bad for my image.

930
00:47:51,852 --> 00:47:53,888
LORNA: I'm afraid I insist.
RIGGS: Oh, you insist?

931
00:47:53,972 --> 00:47:57,681
In that case, let's find someplace private.
Step into my orifice.

932
00:48:03,572 --> 00:48:06,370
RIGGS: Hey, Becker, how's it hanging?
BECKER: Hey, Riggs.

933
00:48:06,452 --> 00:48:08,204
BECKER: Clip any wrong wires lately?

934
00:48:08,292 --> 00:48:10,522
RIGGS: I haven't done that
for a couple days.

935
00:48:10,612 --> 00:48:12,648
Next time, wait for the bomb squad.

936
00:48:12,732 --> 00:48:13,881
BECKER: Yeah, it's our job.

937
00:48:13,972 --> 00:48:16,406
I'll remember that.
We saved a cat, though.

938
00:48:16,532 --> 00:48:18,204
Great. I love cats.

939
00:48:20,252 --> 00:48:21,765
RIGGS: Go ahead, talk. I'm listening.

940
00:48:21,852 --> 00:48:26,004
