concerning a case under my investigation.

941
00:48:26,092 --> 00:48:27,491
Damn right, I did.

942
00:48:27,572 --> 00:48:29,005
BECKER: Careful, she's Internal Affairs.

943
00:48:29,092 --> 00:48:31,845
You had a tip on Travis.
You should have shared it with me.

944
00:48:31,932 --> 00:48:33,445
No, I take that back.

945
00:48:33,532 --> 00:48:35,921
You were required to share it with me.

946
00:48:36,292 --> 00:48:38,760
I was "required" to share it with you?

947
00:48:38,852 --> 00:48:40,683
I don't have to share shit with you.

948
00:48:40,772 --> 00:48:43,844
School yard rules: If you don't scratch
my back, I don't throw you...

949
00:48:43,932 --> 00:48:46,082
LORNA: Oh, come on, Riggs.
I can't do that!

950
00:48:46,172 --> 00:48:47,321
RIGGS: Yes, you can!

951
00:48:47,412 --> 00:48:49,642
Why don't you cut out
this classified bullshit!

952
00:48:49,732 --> 00:48:52,007
Right now! It's giving me the shits!

953
00:48:52,092 --> 00:48:55,164
We're cops. You're a cop, I'm a cop.
We're both on the same side, right?

954
00:48:55,252 --> 00:48:56,401
RIGGS: Right?
LORNA: Right!

955
00:48:56,492 --> 00:48:59,131
Good! Why don't we start to act like it.

956
00:48:59,292 --> 00:49:03,205
There are kids out there. Babies. No
brains, but they got automatic weapons.

957
00:49:03,292 --> 00:49:05,567
RIGGS: Yesterday,
my partner nailed this kid...

958
00:49:05,652 --> 00:49:07,210
I know about Murtaugh.

959
00:49:08,892 --> 00:49:10,883
Yeah. And I'm sorry, Riggs.

960
00:49:11,972 --> 00:49:12,882
Yeah.

961
00:49:14,652 --> 00:49:16,131
[Sighs deeply]

962
00:49:18,012 --> 00:49:20,446
Why don't you let me in on this?
I can help you.

963
00:49:20,532 --> 00:49:23,490
I really want to help you,
if you'll let me. Let me.

964
00:49:23,772 --> 00:49:26,002
What do you say? Have we got a deal?

965
00:49:29,652 --> 00:49:31,051
Wash your hands...

966
00:49:33,492 --> 00:49:35,608
...and meet me in my office.

967
00:49:36,452 --> 00:49:37,567
Yeah.

968
00:49:38,132 --> 00:49:39,884
RIGGS: I'll be right there.

969
00:49:41,212 --> 00:49:42,691
I'll be right there.

970
00:49:43,092 --> 00:49:45,003
LORNA: MAC-10, 9 mm, semi-automatic...

971
00:49:45,092 --> 00:49:48,528
BOTH: Converted to automatic
with 36 rounds in the magazine.

972
00:49:48,612 --> 00:49:50,250
"On a sesame seed bun."

973
00:49:50,332 --> 00:49:51,731
Very illegal.

974
00:49:51,932 --> 00:49:53,729
The gun has a history.
Wanna know about it?

975
00:49:53,812 --> 00:49:54,801
Tell me.

976
00:49:57,812 --> 00:50:00,929
"Killed a convenience store clerk
in LA County, July 1990.

977
00:50:01,012 --> 00:50:04,721
"Used in a drive-by shooting
in San Bernardino County, August 1990.

978
00:50:05,372 --> 00:50:09,650
"Confiscated by a truant officer
of the LA School Board, October 1990."

979
00:50:10,292 --> 00:50:12,760
Scheduled for destruction by LAPD
six weeks ago.

980
00:50:12,852 --> 00:50:14,763
"Scheduled for destruction?"

981
00:50:15,412 --> 00:50:17,323
LORNA: But it never got there.

982
00:50:19,292 --> 00:50:22,204
Instead, it found its way
into the hands of a 15-year-old boy...

983
00:50:22,292 --> 00:50:24,601
...who fired it on a police officer,
your partner.

984
00:50:24,692 --> 00:50:25,841
I thought it looked familiar.

985
00:50:25,932 --> 00:50:27,888
LORNA:
That gun and 15,000 others like it...

986
00:50:27,972 --> 00:50:31,521
...were stolen from a police storage facility
before they could be destroyed.

987
00:50:31,612 --> 00:50:34,206
<i>They should be paper clips right now,</i>
<i>or license plates.</i>

988
00:50:34,292 --> 00:50:38,205
Anything but a gun. Here we are
busting our asses on the streets...

989
00:50:38,332 --> 00:50:42,371
...getting these weapons out of circulation
and now they're headed back out.

990
00:50:42,452 --> 00:50:46,968
By busting Phelps, you stumbled onto
something the LAPD's tried to keep quiet.

991
00:50:47,212 --> 00:50:50,568
That's why Internal Affairs is onto this.
They think this is an inside job.

992
00:50:50,652 --> 00:50:53,246
LORNA: That's right.
They knew police procedures.

993
00:50:53,332 --> 00:50:55,527
They knew where the guns were stored
and how to get in.

994
00:50:55,612 --> 00:50:58,001
They even knew the sorting codes
on the containers...

995
00:50:58,092 --> 00:51:00,731
...because they took the automatics
and left the junk behind.

996
00:51:00,812 --> 00:51:03,485
LORNA: It all pointed to a cop.
RIGGS: Or an ex-cop.

997
00:51:03,572 --> 00:51:04,402
Right.

998
00:51:04,492 --> 00:51:05,686
BOTH: Travis.

999
00:51:08,172 --> 00:51:10,640
And you let him slip through your fingers.

1000
00:51:11,372 --> 00:51:13,203
That's closer than you ever got.

1001
00:51:13,292 --> 00:51:14,725
Close, Riggs?

1002
00:51:14,892 --> 00:51:17,690
Close is a lingerie shop
without a front window.

1003
00:51:20,332 --> 00:51:21,845
Do you want to go for a ride?

1004
00:51:21,932 --> 00:51:23,604
Sure, where are we going?

1005
00:51:24,012 --> 00:51:25,650
LORNA: It's a surprise.

1006
00:51:30,012 --> 00:51:31,161
Oh, I love surprises.

1007
00:51:32,172 --> 00:51:33,605
RIGGS: What is this place?

1008
00:51:33,692 --> 00:51:35,967
LORNA: I accessed Billy Phelps'
phone records on my computer.

1009
00:51:36,052 --> 00:51:38,168
LORNA: He made a dozen calls
to this address.

1010
00:51:38,252 --> 00:51:40,368
RIGGS: That was nice of you
to steal that information.

1011
00:51:40,452 --> 00:51:42,363
LORNA: Semantics, Riggs.
RIGGS: "Semantics"?

1012
00:51:42,452 --> 00:51:44,647
RIGGS: I'm always up for some antics.

1013
00:51:45,052 --> 00:51:46,724
Let's go on three.

1014
00:51:47,052 --> 00:51:48,007
LORNA: One.

1015
00:51:48,092 --> 00:51:50,242
RIGGS: On three, or three and then go?
LORNA: What?

1016
00:51:50,332 --> 00:51:52,323
Never mind. One, two, three.

1017
00:51:54,892 --> 00:51:56,371
LORNA: I've got you.

1018
00:52:05,932 --> 00:52:07,684
[Ferocious growling]

1019
00:52:09,332 --> 00:52:11,687
It looks like Billy's grandmother
owns a big dog.

1020
00:52:11,772 --> 00:52:13,649
It's not a dog. It's a horse.

1021
00:52:13,732 --> 00:52:15,404
LORNA: I hate dogs, Riggs.

1022
00:52:16,092 --> 00:52:17,286
I don't get it.

1023
00:52:17,412 --> 00:52:20,722
You don't get what?
It's a dog. It's a fucking dog.

1024
00:52:20,972 --> 00:52:25,443
I don't get, "Close, is a lingerie shop
without a front window." I don't get it.

1025
00:52:25,532 --> 00:52:26,567
Later.

1026
00:52:27,652 --> 00:52:28,971
[Growling]

1027
00:52:31,492 --> 00:52:32,845
What're you doing?

1028
00:52:33,092 --> 00:52:35,811
I can't shoot a dog.
People, okay, but not dogs.

1029
00:52:36,252 --> 00:52:38,482
I should try to make friends with him.

1030
00:52:38,652 --> 00:52:39,926
Make friends?

1031
00:52:40,972 --> 00:52:44,408
Now don't run, because he'll only
chase you down and kill you.

1032
00:52:46,732 --> 00:52:48,085
RIGGS: Here, boy.

1033
00:52:48,172 --> 00:52:49,207
Here, boy.

1034
00:52:50,212 --> 00:52:52,203
[Low aggressive growling]

1035
00:52:56,772 --> 00:52:57,363
Shit!

1036
00:52:57,452 --> 00:52:58,646
Good boy!

1037
00:52:59,372 --> 00:53:01,966
[Dog barks and growls,
Riggs whimpers]

1038
00:53:06,532 --> 00:53:07,601
Riggs?

1039
00:53:09,052 --> 00:53:10,531
[Riggs growls]

1040
00:53:12,572 --> 00:53:13,925
You're crazy.

1041
00:53:15,572 --> 00:53:17,608
[Riggs pants and whimpers]

1042
00:53:33,212 --> 00:53:34,531
Want some?

1043
00:53:34,812 --> 00:53:36,370
RIGGS: Are you hungry?

1044
00:53:37,532 --> 00:53:39,124
You're a hungry boy.

1045
00:53:39,252 --> 00:53:41,482
Doesn't anybody feed you? Come on.

1046
00:53:44,332 --> 00:53:46,323
Here's more. Leave some for me.

1047
00:53:46,652 --> 00:53:50,088
RIGGS: Very slowly, as if you're not here,
just walk away.

1048
00:53:50,492 --> 00:53:51,527
You want me to go?

1049
00:53:51,612 --> 00:53:53,364
Yeah. This is a guy sort of thing.

1050
00:53:53,452 --> 00:53:54,965
LORNA: "Guy sort of thing?"

1051
00:53:55,052 --> 00:53:56,565
RIGGS: Are you alone?

1052
00:54:05,132 --> 00:54:06,201
Stay, stay.

1053
00:54:08,252 --> 00:54:10,083
HATCHETT: Come on, let's go.

1054
00:54:30,172 --> 00:54:31,446
HATCHETT: How many is that?

1055
00:54:31,532 --> 00:54:35,207
- <i>Fifty-five.</i>
- Fifty-five. All right, we've got eight more.

1056
00:54:35,452 --> 00:54:37,522
We'll get these later. Let's go.

1057
00:54:41,052 --> 00:54:42,371
Hi, fellas.

1058
00:54:43,132 --> 00:54:44,804
What's in all these boxes?

1059
00:54:45,692 --> 00:54:47,125
[Riggs wails]

1060
00:54:49,252 --> 00:54:50,321
[Thump]

1061
00:54:54,732 --> 00:54:58,930
HATCHETT: Easy, let's not kill him, yet.
Let's see who he is first, all right?

1062
00:55:00,812 --> 00:55:02,609
[Gasping] You have the right
to remain silent.

1063
00:55:02,692 --> 00:55:04,330
HATCHETT: Shut him up!

1064
00:55:04,692 --> 00:55:06,603
"Sergeant Martin Riggs."

1065
00:55:08,932 --> 00:55:10,650
- Get the truck ready.
- Right.

1066
00:55:10,732 --> 00:55:12,290
So, Sergeant Riggs...

1067
00:55:12,532 --> 00:55:14,045
<i>... how did you find us?</i>

1068
00:55:14,132 --> 00:55:15,724
Freeze! Police!

1069
00:55:16,692 --> 00:55:18,091
Another one?

1070
00:55:18,412 --> 00:55:20,084
We need a new fucking dog.

1071
00:55:20,172 --> 00:55:21,890
Get your hands up, asshole.

1072
00:55:22,132 --> 00:55:23,406
Get them up!

1073
00:55:24,852 --> 00:55:26,331
[Coughs and gasps]

1074
00:55:26,892 --> 00:55:27,961
A little bit higher.

1075
00:55:28,052 --> 00:55:29,246
LORNA: That's better.

1076
00:55:29,332 --> 00:55:30,481
[Coughs]

1077
00:55:30,572 --> 00:55:31,846
Very good.

1078
00:55:35,692 --> 00:55:36,841
Drop it, miss.

1079
00:55:39,052 --> 00:55:40,405
RIGGS: Now, look!

1080
00:56:15,452 --> 00:56:17,090
[Car engine revs]

1081
00:56:17,452 --> 00:56:18,965
[Tires screech]

1082
00:56:26,892 --> 00:56:28,848
RIGGS: Okay, I'm on! No, I'm not!

1083
00:56:28,932 --> 00:56:29,762
<i>Wait!</i>

1084
00:56:30,092 --> 00:56:31,445
<i>Wait, wait!</i>

1085
00:56:34,772 --> 00:56:36,205
RIGGS: Sergeant Cole!

1086
00:56:36,292 --> 00:56:37,930
Get down! Get down!

1087
00:56:38,772 --> 00:56:41,240
[Multiple gunshots whizz, glass shatters]

1088
00:56:41,612 --> 00:56:44,126
HATCHETT: Get those cases
and kill that dog!

1089
00:56:47,052 --> 00:56:48,371
[Tires screech]

1090
00:56:50,932 --> 00:56:51,887
[Gunshots]

1091
00:56:51,972 --> 00:56:53,405
[Dog barking]

1092
00:56:54,692 --> 00:56:55,841
RIGGS: Stop!

1093
00:56:56,332 --> 00:57:00,086
- The dog. Where'd you learn to fight?
- Catholic school. Forget the dog!

1094
00:57:00,172 --> 00:57:02,049
RIGGS: Here, boy!
We're waiting for the dog!

1095
00:57:02,132 --> 00:57:04,248
RIGGS: Hold it, hold it. Hurry up!

1096
00:57:04,692 --> 00:57:06,762
Good dog. Good puppy. Go!

1097
00:57:09,332 --> 00:57:10,401
Stop!

1098
00:57:11,012 --> 00:57:12,331
LORNA: What?
RIGGS: Guns.

1099
00:57:12,412 --> 00:57:13,401
RIGGS: It's full of guns.
LORNA: Grab one!

1100
00:57:13,492 --> 00:57:15,244
RIGGS: You grab one!
LORNA: Chicken.

1101
00:57:15,332 --> 00:57:16,731
RIGGS: Step on it.

1102
00:57:17,052 --> 00:57:18,371
[Gunshots]

1103
00:57:20,252 --> 00:57:22,243
Get that crate! Come on!

1104
00:57:25,172 --> 00:57:26,605
[Dog barking]

1105
00:57:27,852 --> 00:57:30,571
TYRONE: <i>Hatchett, you said not to worry</i>
<i>about the police...</i>

1106
00:57:30,652 --> 00:57:32,210
<i>... but the cops are all over you!</i>

1107
00:57:32,292 --> 00:57:34,806
<i>They got my guns.</i>
<i>They'll come after me, next!</i>

1108
00:57:34,892 --> 00:57:36,848
As far as I'm concerned, the deal's off!

1109
00:57:36,932 --> 00:57:39,924
Get a grip on yourself, Tyrone.
We have a deal.

1110
00:57:40,172 --> 00:57:41,525
Nobody backs out.

1111
00:57:41,652 --> 00:57:43,643
TYRONE: <i>You said you had the cops</i>
<i>under control.</i>

1112
00:57:43,732 --> 00:57:45,723
I see that isn't so. Give me one reason...

1113
00:57:45,812 --> 00:57:47,291
TYRONE:
<i>... why I should do business with you.</i>

1114
00:57:47,372 --> 00:57:48,930
I'll give you a good reason.

1115
00:57:49,012 --> 00:57:50,923
Tyrone, this is Travis.

1116
00:57:51,252 --> 00:57:55,404
You back out now, and I'll make sure
only your dentist can identify the body.

1117
00:57:55,492 --> 00:57:57,881
Is that a good enough reason for you?

1118
00:58:00,052 --> 00:58:01,610
But I need ammo!

1119
00:58:01,732 --> 00:58:03,768
I'm out of business without ammo!

1120
00:58:03,852 --> 00:58:05,080
I need the good stuff.

1121
00:58:05,172 --> 00:58:07,402
You'll get the ammo. The good stuff.

1122
00:58:08,852 --> 00:58:10,444
"The good stuff." Jesus.

1123
00:58:10,532 --> 00:58:12,045
JACK: Time to pay
another visit to the LAPD.

1124
00:58:14,692 --> 00:58:16,489
You look like I feel.

1125
00:58:26,252 --> 00:58:27,128
Hey?

1126
00:58:29,212 --> 00:58:31,567
RIGGS: Have you got anything
I can put on my head?

1127
00:58:31,652 --> 00:58:33,051
The hat in the closet.

1128
00:58:33,132 --> 00:58:36,966
You're all heart. Here I thought
you'd get all tender and maternal.

1129
00:58:37,772 --> 00:58:39,842
I was raised with four brothers.

1130
00:58:40,012 --> 00:58:44,483
We got hurt often, but if no bones were
broken or blood gushed, nobody cared.

1131
00:58:44,572 --> 00:58:45,971
Look, blood. See? Blood.

1132
00:58:46,052 --> 00:58:47,565
LORNA: It's not gushing.

1133
00:58:47,652 --> 00:58:49,768
RIGGS: It was free falling earlier.

1134
00:58:50,212 --> 00:58:54,683
Could you bring me a needle and thread?
Some peroxide. I'll patch it up myself.

1135
00:58:57,452 --> 00:58:58,965
Don't touch anything.

1136
00:58:59,052 --> 00:59:00,326
I wasn't.

1137
00:59:02,012 --> 00:59:03,604
What's with you?

1138
00:59:16,332 --> 00:59:18,607
[<i>Three Stooges</i> theme music plays
on computer]

1139
00:59:18,692 --> 00:59:21,331
RIGGS: Boys.
LORNA: What are you doing?

1140
00:59:21,612 --> 00:59:23,842
LORNA: I said not to touch anything.
RIGGS: It came on by itself.

1141
00:59:23,932 --> 00:59:26,082
All by itself. What are you, a wise guy?

1142
00:59:26,172 --> 00:59:28,163
RIGGS: You don't like to share your toys?

1143
00:59:28,252 --> 00:59:30,083
- This isn't a toy.
- What is it?

1144
00:59:30,172 --> 00:59:32,003
- This is a weapon.
- A weapon?

1145
00:59:32,092 --> 00:59:34,322
Used properly, a very effective weapon.

1146
00:59:34,412 --> 00:59:36,323
What, do you throw it at people?

1147
00:59:36,412 --> 00:59:39,131
LORNA: You'll give yourself a hernia.
Come here. Sit down.

1148
00:59:39,212 --> 00:59:40,327
LORNA: Right here.

1149
00:59:40,412 --> 00:59:43,324
RIGGS: Take a little off the top.
LORNA: Right here.

1150
00:59:48,332 --> 00:59:50,641
RIGGS: Do you bring
all your interrogations home?

1151
00:59:50,732 --> 00:59:52,962
LORNA: What are we talking about?
RIGGS: It's back here.

1152
00:59:53,052 --> 00:59:54,690
RIGGS: Careful, careful.
LORNA: Turn your head.

1153
00:59:54,772 --> 00:59:56,205
RIGGS: Careful.
LORNA: This?

1154
00:59:56,292 --> 00:59:59,011
LORNA: This scratch?
RIGGS: It feels like the Grand Canyon.

1155
00:59:59,092 --> 01:00:00,286
Oh, God.

1156
01:00:00,732 --> 01:00:01,926
Hold still.

1157
01:00:03,092 --> 01:00:05,526
LORNA: Oh, God. We haven't even started.

1158
01:00:06,332 --> 01:00:07,845
Be gentle with me.

1159
01:00:08,252 --> 01:00:11,608
I see this isn't virgin territory.
What is this? A knife?

1160
01:00:11,772 --> 01:00:14,650
That's an ax.
Some guy mistook my head for a log.

1161
01:00:14,892 --> 01:00:17,360
- That's a natural mistake.
- What, I have a wooden head?

1162
01:00:17,452 --> 01:00:18,771
- Look at that.
- A knife.

1163
01:00:18,852 --> 01:00:20,570
Knife? That's very nice.

1164
01:00:21,252 --> 01:00:22,207
This is all right.

1165
01:00:22,292 --> 01:00:24,681
That's pavement, dragged down Crenshaw.

1166
01:00:24,812 --> 01:00:27,610
That's great. Look at that texture.
Look at this.

1167
01:00:27,852 --> 01:00:29,843
Same thing. Third and Highland.

1168
01:00:29,972 --> 01:00:32,691
RIGGS: Dragged for about half a block.
LORNA: That's a good one.

1169
01:00:32,772 --> 01:00:34,967
Feel that texture. Cheese-grater time.

1170
01:00:35,052 --> 01:00:37,088
RIGGS: Moving truck.
LORNA: Moving truck?

1171
01:00:37,172 --> 01:00:38,048
Moving bullet.

1172
01:00:38,132 --> 01:00:40,600
RIGGS: Moving bullet?
LORNA: Here. This is the best.

1173
01:00:40,692 --> 01:00:42,728
It goes all the way through to the back.

1174
01:00:42,812 --> 01:00:44,006
RIGGS: Right through?

1175
01:00:44,092 --> 01:00:45,764
You're lucky. Was it a.22?

1176
01:00:45,852 --> 01:00:47,126
It's a.38.

1177
01:00:47,452 --> 01:00:50,205
That's a.38? That's wimpy.
This is a.38.

1178
01:00:50,292 --> 01:00:52,806
Yours is bigger than mine?
I don't think so.

1179
01:00:53,252 --> 01:00:54,571
Maybe not, but look.

1180
01:00:54,652 --> 01:00:57,120
A whole family of.44s on the back.

1181
01:00:57,852 --> 01:00:58,967
RIGGS: There they are.

1182
01:00:59,052 --> 01:00:59,848
LORNA: That's impressive.

1183
01:00:59,932 --> 01:01:03,288
One hit my lung. I was breathing
blood bubbles. It was disgusting.

1184
01:01:03,372 --> 01:01:04,600
Blood bubbles. Okay.

1185
01:01:04,692 --> 01:01:06,125
RIGGS: You got one?

1186
01:01:06,732 --> 01:01:08,404
Pump-action. 12-gauge.

1187
01:01:10,492 --> 01:01:12,767
LORNA: Right down here. Went through.

1188
01:01:13,132 --> 01:01:14,451
RIGGS: That must have hurt.
LORNA: Right.

1189
01:01:14,532 --> 01:01:15,487
Not too close.

1190
01:01:15,572 --> 01:01:17,563
Riggs, if he were that close, I'd be dead.

1191
01:01:17,652 --> 01:01:19,608
I can beat it. I can beat it.

1192
01:01:20,572 --> 01:01:22,688
- I'll take your word for it.
- You gotta see this.

1193
01:01:22,772 --> 01:01:24,285
LORNA: I believe you.
RIGGS: This guy had a knife.

1194
01:01:24,372 --> 01:01:28,445
RIGGS: You'll love it. He stuck it in my leg
and ran it around eight times.

1195
01:01:29,052 --> 01:01:31,168
LORNA: I'll take your word for it.
RIGGS: Look!

1196
01:01:31,252 --> 01:01:32,367
No, I said forget it.

1197
01:01:32,452 --> 01:01:34,010
This is a blue-ribbon event.

1198
01:01:34,092 --> 01:01:35,445
Forget it, Riggs.

1199
01:01:36,332 --> 01:01:37,367
You started this.

1200
01:01:37,452 --> 01:01:40,171
LORNA: Yeah, I can end it.
RIGGS: You know what?

1201
01:01:40,492 --> 01:01:42,164
You're a very poor loser.

1202
01:01:43,212 --> 01:01:44,406
I didn't lose.

1203
01:01:44,652 --> 01:01:46,244
RIGGS: Yes, you did.
LORNA: No, I didn't lose.

1204
01:01:46,332 --> 01:01:47,924
RIGGS: You lost.
LORNA: I conceded.

1205
01:01:48,012 --> 01:01:50,321
No, I conceded. There's a difference
between losing and conceding.

1206
01:01:50,412 --> 01:01:52,368
You conceded or you're conceited?

1207
01:01:52,452 --> 01:01:54,408
LORNA: You think I'm conceited?
RIGGS: Yeah.

1208
01:01:54,492 --> 01:01:56,562
Tell me you lost. Admit to it.

1209
01:01:56,652 --> 01:01:57,767
I'll get you a Band-Aid.

1210
01:01:57,852 --> 01:02:01,049
RIGGS: Tell me you lost.
LORNA: I said, "don't touch anything."

1211
01:02:01,132 --> 01:02:03,726
[Soft instrumental music, background]

1212
01:02:12,092 --> 01:02:14,811
You're going to smack
the shit out of me, right?

1213
01:02:15,372 --> 01:02:17,203
I can do better than that.

1214
01:02:33,612 --> 01:02:36,251
This could be a serious ethical breach here.

1215
01:02:36,732 --> 01:02:38,962
RIGGS: I never made it
with another sergeant before.

1216
01:02:39,052 --> 01:02:40,280
Shut up, Riggs.

1217
01:02:56,212 --> 01:02:58,806
[Soft instrumental music, background]

1218
01:03:02,372 --> 01:03:03,771
[Dog whines]

1219
01:03:33,852 --> 01:03:35,285
[Riggs gasps]

1220
01:03:36,892 --> 01:03:38,484
Oh, damn, Riggs.

1221
01:03:41,132 --> 01:03:42,008
ROGER: What do you want?

1222
01:03:42,092 --> 01:03:44,481
I just wanted to see how you were doing.

1223
01:03:44,572 --> 01:03:46,324
Who sent you? Trish?

1224
01:03:46,852 --> 01:03:48,729
You're doing pretty well.
Trish didn't send me.

1225
01:03:48,812 --> 01:03:51,087
Rianne came to see me.
She asked me to find you.

1226
01:03:51,172 --> 01:03:52,491
To your place?

1227
01:03:52,572 --> 01:03:53,800
Well, that's where I am.

1228
01:03:53,892 --> 01:03:56,645
- My daughter came to your trailer?
- Yeah.

1229
01:03:58,012 --> 01:04:01,800
- My daughter came to your trailer?
- Come on, she was worried.

1230
01:04:02,332 --> 01:04:04,129
Get off of my boat, Riggs!

1231
01:04:04,212 --> 01:04:06,043
- Come on.
- Get off my boat!

1232
01:04:06,132 --> 01:04:07,565
You're drunk.

1233
01:04:07,692 --> 01:04:09,808
That's something you should know about.

1234
01:04:09,892 --> 01:04:12,531
- This isn't going to do you any good.
- Give me that.

1235
01:04:12,612 --> 01:04:13,647
Give me that.

1236
01:04:13,732 --> 01:04:15,609
Roger, please don't do this.

1237
01:04:15,932 --> 01:04:18,765
You got three days until you retire.
This won't do you any good.

1238
01:04:18,852 --> 01:04:21,207
You self-righteous bastard! Give it...

1239
01:04:21,612 --> 01:04:23,409
Don't do this, okay? Please?

1240
01:04:23,492 --> 01:04:25,289
Give it to me, damn it.

1241
01:04:25,892 --> 01:04:28,281
What are you going to do now, shoot me?

1242
01:04:29,532 --> 01:04:30,567
There.

1243
01:04:30,652 --> 01:04:32,847
Take your finger out of my bottle.
Give me that gun.

1244
01:04:32,932 --> 01:04:34,650
The bottle's going sailing.

1245
01:04:35,612 --> 01:04:37,091
Son of a bitch!

1246
01:04:37,572 --> 01:04:38,641
[Thud]

1247
01:04:41,572 --> 01:04:43,051
Not bad for an old man.

1248
01:04:43,132 --> 01:04:44,042
Are you finished?

1249
01:04:44,132 --> 01:04:46,771
No, I got another bottle in the galley
and I'm gonna get it.

1250
01:04:46,852 --> 01:04:48,080
No, you're not.

1251
01:04:48,172 --> 01:04:50,208
RIGGS: Don't do this to yourself!

1252
01:04:50,292 --> 01:04:51,884
You gotta cut this out.

1253
01:04:53,092 --> 01:04:55,162
Oh, man, I'm sorry. Are you okay?

1254
01:04:55,652 --> 01:04:57,370
RIGGS: Come on. Sit down.

1255
01:04:58,572 --> 01:05:00,802
ROGER: You hit me.
RIGGS: Cool it, will you?

1256
01:05:00,892 --> 01:05:02,723
Cut it out. Give it up, okay?

1257
01:05:02,812 --> 01:05:03,927
Go ahead.

1258
01:05:04,012 --> 01:05:05,843
Go ahead. Hit me again.

1259
01:05:06,012 --> 01:05:08,128
I don't want to hit you!
You think I like this shit?

1260
01:05:08,212 --> 01:05:10,931
Hit me again. You think I'm afraid of you?

1261
01:05:11,172 --> 01:05:13,561
- I know you're not.
- Of that kung-fu shit?

1262
01:05:13,732 --> 01:05:15,131
Please, Rog.

1263
01:05:16,092 --> 01:05:18,048
That kid was a killer, all right.

1264
01:05:18,132 --> 01:05:19,406
That wasn't a toy in his hand.

1265
01:05:19,492 --> 01:05:22,882
That was a machine pistol
with twin carbines and all the trimmings.

1266
01:05:22,972 --> 01:05:24,007
He would have drilled you...

1267
01:05:24,092 --> 01:05:26,367
...me, anybody that came along.

1268
01:05:26,532 --> 01:05:28,011
You had no choice.

1269
01:05:28,332 --> 01:05:30,562
It didn't happen to you. It happened to me.

1270
01:05:30,652 --> 01:05:32,051
It happened to me!

1271
01:05:32,132 --> 01:05:34,168
My God, I killed that kid!

1272
01:05:34,372 --> 01:05:35,725
ROGER: I killed that boy.

1273
01:05:35,812 --> 01:05:37,689
You've killed a lot of people.

1274
01:05:37,852 --> 01:05:41,208
ROGER: You've killed a fucking
lot of people! You don't kill a baby!

1275
01:05:41,292 --> 01:05:44,443
You've got ice in your veins.
You don't kill a boy like Nick.

1276
01:05:44,532 --> 01:05:46,090
You selfish bastard!

1277
01:05:46,172 --> 01:05:47,651
You selfish bastard!

1278
01:05:47,972 --> 01:05:50,247
You're just thinking about yourself.

1279
01:05:50,372 --> 01:05:51,885
RIGGS: What about me?

1280
01:05:52,292 --> 01:05:54,522
We're partners! We are partners.

1281
01:05:55,452 --> 01:05:57,124
What happens to you, happens to me.

1282
01:05:57,212 --> 01:06:00,363
After all the shit we've been through,
don't you get it?

1283
01:06:00,452 --> 01:06:02,090
RIGGS: Don't you get it?

1284
01:06:02,652 --> 01:06:06,088
When you retire, you're not just
retiring you, you're retiring us.

1285
01:06:06,172 --> 01:06:07,969
RIGGS: You're retiring us.
ROGER: That's not my problem.

1286
01:06:08,052 --> 01:06:09,041
Yes, it is.

1287
01:06:09,132 --> 01:06:11,885
ROGER: It's not my problem!
RIGGS: You're the only family I've got!

1288
01:06:11,972 --> 01:06:14,566
I've got three beautiful kids.
I love them and they're yours!

1289
01:06:14,652 --> 01:06:17,769
Trish does my laundry.
I live in your icebox. I live in your life!

1290
01:06:17,852 --> 01:06:19,683
What am I going to do?

1291
01:06:19,972 --> 01:06:21,371
- I don't care.
- Yes, you do!

1292
01:06:21,452 --> 01:06:22,771
ROGER: I don't care.
RIGGS: Yes, you do!

1293
01:06:22,852 --> 01:06:24,285
ROGER: [Screams] I don't care!

1294
01:06:24,372 --> 01:06:25,441
RIGGS: [Yells] Yes, you do!

1295
01:06:25,532 --> 01:06:27,409
ROGER: I don't care!
RIGGS: You do so!

1296
01:06:27,492 --> 01:06:28,925
I don't care!

1297
01:06:29,052 --> 01:06:31,202
I don't care! I don't care!

1298
01:06:33,852 --> 01:06:37,561
I don't know what I'm saying anymore.
I don't know what I'm thinking.

1299
01:06:38,332 --> 01:06:40,482
I had three days, and now this.

1300
01:06:42,052 --> 01:06:43,087
I'm sorry.

1301
01:06:43,372 --> 01:06:46,330
RIGGS: That's all right.
ROGER: No, I'm really sorry.

1302
01:06:47,412 --> 01:06:48,765
I didn't realize...

1303
01:06:48,852 --> 01:06:50,843
...that my retirement
was gonna screw you up.

1304
01:06:50,932 --> 01:06:54,925
Forget it. I haven't got any problems.
I was out of line saying that shit.

1305
01:06:55,332 --> 01:06:56,526
Look, man...

1306
01:06:57,892 --> 01:06:59,166
Riggs, look...

1307
01:07:00,292 --> 01:07:01,805
You know I love you.

1308
01:07:02,852 --> 01:07:06,686
You know I love you, Riggs.
And your problems are my problems.

1309
01:07:08,132 --> 01:07:10,521
Like you said, what happens to you...

1310
01:07:11,012 --> 01:07:13,003
...happens to me. So try me.

1311
01:07:13,332 --> 01:07:14,970
ROGER: I'm here for you.

1312
01:07:15,292 --> 01:07:17,362
I haven't got any problems.

1313
01:07:18,012 --> 01:07:21,209
Yes, you do. We all have problems.
You help me...

1314
01:07:22,132 --> 01:07:23,850
...and I'm gonna help you.

1315
01:07:26,532 --> 01:07:28,523
I do have a little problem.

1316
01:07:29,972 --> 01:07:32,566
You don't want to hear it.
This is piddly shit.

1317
01:07:32,692 --> 01:07:34,523
Yes, I do. I want to hear it.

1318
01:07:34,612 --> 01:07:36,603
ROGER: Tell me.
RIGGS: This is ridiculous.

1319
01:07:36,692 --> 01:07:39,570
RIGGS: You don't want to hear it.
ROGER: I'm here. I'm here.

1320
01:07:39,652 --> 01:07:40,767
Well...

1321
01:07:41,652 --> 01:07:45,486
I think maybe I slept with someone
that I probably shouldn't have.

1322
01:07:47,332 --> 01:07:48,765
You son of a bitch!

1323
01:07:55,692 --> 01:07:56,761
RIGGS: Help me.

1324
01:07:56,852 --> 01:07:59,082
ROGER: I ought to let you drown,
you traitor.

1325
01:07:59,172 --> 01:08:00,321
RIGGS: Help me.

1326
01:08:00,412 --> 01:08:01,891
RIGGS: Come on in.

1327
01:08:05,852 --> 01:08:07,205
What did you hit me for?

1328
01:08:07,292 --> 01:08:09,169
'Cause you slept with Rianne.

1329
01:08:10,572 --> 01:08:11,607
I did not.

1330
01:08:11,692 --> 01:08:15,002
ROGER: Who did you sleep with?
RIGGS: I slept with Sergeant Cole.

1331
01:08:15,092 --> 01:08:16,730
Sergeant Cole from Traffic?

1332
01:08:16,812 --> 01:08:18,928
No, not Sergeant Cole from Traffic.

1333
01:08:20,012 --> 01:08:21,843
Lorna. Sergeant Cole from Traffic
is her uncle.

1334
01:08:21,932 --> 01:08:24,810
ROGER: Okay. That's okay.
RIGGS: Oh, I don't know.

1335
01:08:26,892 --> 01:08:28,371
SHERIFF: Sheriff's Department.

1336
01:08:28,452 --> 01:08:29,407
Sheriff...

1337
01:08:29,492 --> 01:08:30,845
We're LAPD.

1338
01:08:32,052 --> 01:08:34,566
SHERIFF: What are you boys doing
down there?

1339
01:08:34,732 --> 01:08:37,166
RIGGS: We're in the middle of a case.
ROGER: Yeah.

1340
01:08:37,252 --> 01:08:38,367
Of Scotch.

1341
01:08:40,332 --> 01:08:41,765
SHERIFF: Let's get out of here.

1342
01:08:41,852 --> 01:08:43,331
[Both chuckle]

1343
01:08:56,652 --> 01:08:58,768
ROGER: Go with the grain.
NICK: Huh?

1344
01:09:01,612 --> 01:09:03,443
ROGER: I'll show you. Here.

1345
01:09:05,572 --> 01:09:07,483
You're going against the grain.

1346
01:09:11,972 --> 01:09:13,803
ROGER: Like that.
NICK: Okay.

1347
01:09:20,132 --> 01:09:21,326
Are you okay?

1348
01:09:24,372 --> 01:09:26,363
Darryl was my friend, Dad.

1349
01:09:28,012 --> 01:09:29,968
I know. I'm sorry, Son.

1350
01:09:31,292 --> 01:09:33,169
I hope you don't blame me.

1351
01:09:34,532 --> 01:09:36,124
I don't blame you, Dad.

1352
01:09:37,132 --> 01:09:38,645
NICK: I blame Darryl.

1353
01:09:42,612 --> 01:09:44,250
What's this right here?

1354
01:09:46,572 --> 01:09:48,051
[Roger laughs]

1355
01:09:50,132 --> 01:09:51,645
I love you, Dad.

1356
01:09:54,532 --> 01:09:56,124
I love you, Son.

1357
01:09:57,612 --> 01:10:00,490
[Somber rhythm and blues ballad,
background]

1358
01:10:02,932 --> 01:10:05,400
[Priest conducting funeral service]

1359
01:10:15,972 --> 01:10:19,487
PRIEST: May he find the peace in Heaven
that eluded him on earth.

1360
01:10:19,572 --> 01:10:21,324
And may the scourge of violence...

1361
01:10:21,412 --> 01:10:24,882
<i>... claiming the lives of our children</i>
<i>be lifted by Your grace...</i>

1362
01:10:24,972 --> 01:10:26,564
<i>... and infinite wisdom.</i>

1363
01:10:27,412 --> 01:10:28,527
Amen.

1364
01:10:32,492 --> 01:10:34,483
[Baby crying, background]

1365
01:10:55,492 --> 01:10:56,607
Wait here.

1366
01:11:02,372 --> 01:11:03,771
ROGER: Mrs. Smithers...

1367
01:11:03,852 --> 01:11:05,046
ROGER: Ma'am?

1368
01:11:08,252 --> 01:11:09,970
ROGER: I just don't know...

1369
01:11:10,732 --> 01:11:12,723
[Baby crying, background]

1370
01:11:16,092 --> 01:11:18,526
You want to do something,
Sergeant Murtaugh?

1371
01:11:18,612 --> 01:11:20,011
You find the man...

1372
01:11:20,092 --> 01:11:22,287
...that put the gun in my son's hand.

1373
01:11:39,892 --> 01:11:41,610
Take your mama to the car.

1374
01:11:44,492 --> 01:11:45,686
[Sighs deeply]

1375
01:11:46,332 --> 01:11:47,526
Are you okay?

1376
01:11:48,172 --> 01:11:49,127
Yeah.

1377
01:11:49,932 --> 01:11:51,285
Who's got the gun?

1378
01:11:53,052 --> 01:11:54,246
RIGGS: You got it.
ROGER: Yeah.

1379
01:11:55,412 --> 01:11:56,686
[Banging]

1380
01:11:59,052 --> 01:12:00,644
[Roger grunting]

1381
01:12:01,692 --> 01:12:04,445
- Where did this gun come from?
- Fuck you!

1382
01:12:05,612 --> 01:12:08,922
Ever heard of the word "genocide"?
Have you, stupid motherfucker?

1383
01:12:09,012 --> 01:12:10,604
Have you ever heard of genocide?

1384
01:12:10,692 --> 01:12:13,160
ROGER: You fools are killing yourselves!
You're killing us!

1385
01:12:13,252 --> 01:12:15,243
<i>I'm tired of it! I'm tired of it!</i>
<i>Motherfucker!</i>

1386
01:12:15,332 --> 01:12:18,768
You'd better tell me where this come from
or I'll blow your head off!

1387
01:12:18,852 --> 01:12:21,366
I want to know, now!
Where did it come from?

1388
01:12:24,932 --> 01:12:26,411
[Roger grunts]

1389
01:12:27,532 --> 01:12:30,968
Do you see this gun? I want to know
where it came from! Now!

1390
01:12:33,572 --> 01:12:35,642
We're looking for your friend, Travis.

1391
01:12:35,732 --> 01:12:37,324
I've never heard of him.

1392
01:12:37,812 --> 01:12:39,245
RIGGS: Wrong answer.

1393
01:12:39,332 --> 01:12:41,288
You're pulling on the wrong string.

1394
01:12:41,372 --> 01:12:43,203
That's not a very professional attitude.

1395
01:12:43,292 --> 01:12:44,441
Who the fuck are you guys?

1396
01:12:44,532 --> 01:12:47,524
RIGGS: Sorry! LAPD.
We're just doing a few routine inquiries.

1397
01:12:47,612 --> 01:12:50,046
Have you been checked for lumps recently?

1398
01:12:50,372 --> 01:12:51,487
Give me my fucking wallet!

1399
01:12:51,572 --> 01:12:53,210
ROGER: Keep your hands down!

1400
01:12:53,292 --> 01:12:54,327
HUBY: My fucking wallet!

1401
01:12:54,412 --> 01:12:56,528
ROGER: Get up. We don't need this!

1402
01:12:57,972 --> 01:13:02,170
We have a license that belongs to
Hubert Bartholomew Smith. Nice picture.

1403
01:13:02,292 --> 01:13:03,042
HUBY: Fuck you.

1404
01:13:03,132 --> 01:13:05,123
RIGGS: Hey, there's a lady here.

1405
01:13:06,972 --> 01:13:08,849
What the hell's going on here?

1406
01:13:09,812 --> 01:13:11,803
RIGGS: Maybe they know something.
LORNA: I'll go find out.

1407
01:13:11,892 --> 01:13:14,850
RIGGS: Want me to come with you?
LORNA: No, I got it.

1408
01:13:16,812 --> 01:13:17,927
Maybe I should go with her.

1409
01:13:18,012 --> 01:13:21,368
No, I want you to see something.
She has a gift. Watch this.

1410
01:13:21,812 --> 01:13:23,211
Good morning, gentlemen.

1411
01:13:23,292 --> 01:13:25,362
LAPD. Got a few questions.

1412
01:13:25,492 --> 01:13:26,561
RIGGS: Are you on parole?

1413
01:13:26,652 --> 01:13:29,007
HUBY: I got a job!
RIGGS: Who asked you?

1414
01:13:29,492 --> 01:13:31,289
Do any of you know a Mr. Travis?

1415
01:13:31,372 --> 01:13:32,725
You got a warrant?

1416
01:13:32,892 --> 01:13:34,450
No, but I can get one.

1417
01:13:34,532 --> 01:13:35,521
THUG: Until you do...

1418
01:13:35,612 --> 01:13:36,761
...fuck off.

1419
01:13:37,332 --> 01:13:39,527
That's not a nice thing to say to a lady.

1420
01:13:39,612 --> 01:13:40,886
Fuck you.

1421
01:13:41,172 --> 01:13:42,491
I don't think so.

1422
01:13:45,812 --> 01:13:47,006
Backspin kick.

1423
01:13:48,772 --> 01:13:50,251
[Lorna groans]

1424
01:13:52,452 --> 01:13:53,646
[Man screams]

1425
01:13:56,292 --> 01:13:57,566
Are you okay, honey?

1426
01:13:57,652 --> 01:13:58,767
Just great.

1427
01:13:59,052 --> 01:14:00,883
[Arm snaps, man wails]

1428
01:14:03,572 --> 01:14:04,766
[Crash]

1429
01:14:05,052 --> 01:14:06,804
RIGGS: "Honey?"
LORNA: How are you doing?

1430
01:14:06,892 --> 01:14:08,405
This guy's on parole.

1431
01:14:08,652 --> 01:14:10,449
LORNA: This guy's an asshole!

1432
01:14:10,532 --> 01:14:12,762
- Riggs, there's five of them!
- I know.

1433
01:14:15,012 --> 01:14:16,161
Look at that.

1434
01:14:18,212 --> 01:14:20,442
[Lorna grunts, glass shatters]

1435
01:14:24,172 --> 01:14:25,685
Grabbed his clusters!

1436
01:14:27,692 --> 01:14:28,966
Let me help her.

1437
01:14:29,612 --> 01:14:30,681
Stay still.

1438
01:14:31,052 --> 01:14:32,485
[Man bellows]

1439
01:14:37,892 --> 01:14:39,041
[Thud]

1440
01:14:39,932 --> 01:14:41,126
Hey! Ooh...

1441
01:14:43,292 --> 01:14:44,725
[Chuckles] My girl.

1442
01:14:46,492 --> 01:14:48,289
This PMS... is murder.

1443
01:14:50,092 --> 01:14:51,525
I know what you mean.

1444
01:14:51,612 --> 01:14:53,603
I've been married 25 years.

1445
01:14:54,252 --> 01:14:55,924
So, tell me about Travis.

1446
01:14:56,332 --> 01:14:59,165
I told you before, moron,
I don't know Jack Travis.

1447
01:14:59,252 --> 01:15:00,731
I didn't say his name was Jack.

1448
01:15:00,812 --> 01:15:02,450
You better start telling me
more than jackshit.

1449
01:15:03,132 --> 01:15:04,360
RIGGS: Come on.

1450
01:15:06,492 --> 01:15:09,928
- Men cross the street when they see me.
- I didn't have enough time.

1451
01:15:10,012 --> 01:15:13,288
I'm not your enemy, Captain.
I'm just trying to do my job.

1452
01:15:13,772 --> 01:15:16,730
- Have you eaten?
- I already ate. I've gotta go downtown.

1453
01:15:16,812 --> 01:15:18,803
- What, do you eat alone?
- I'm used to it.

1454
01:15:18,892 --> 01:15:20,086
MURPHY: It's bad for the digestion.

1455
01:15:20,172 --> 01:15:23,244
Tomorrow, you'll have lunch with me,
but I'm not paying.

1456
01:15:25,012 --> 01:15:27,082
[Sirens blaring in distance]

1457
01:15:29,692 --> 01:15:31,125
Are you all right?

1458
01:15:31,932 --> 01:15:33,604
Two fingers, Murph.

1459
01:15:34,812 --> 01:15:38,327
- Jack, what the fuck?
- Get in the car. I'll tell you on the way.

1460
01:15:44,572 --> 01:15:47,291
ROGER: After watching Lorna
handle herself so well...

1461
01:15:47,372 --> 01:15:49,647
...I'm changing my mind about kung fu.

1462
01:15:49,732 --> 01:15:51,370
Want to try it sometime?

1463
01:15:51,652 --> 01:15:53,085
- No.
- Come on.

1464
01:15:53,452 --> 01:15:55,761
You can't teach an old dog new tricks.

1465
01:15:55,972 --> 01:15:57,325
Old dog, my ass.

1466
01:15:58,172 --> 01:16:01,289
Let me try something. Watch this.
It's called a backspin kick.

1467
01:16:01,372 --> 01:16:03,727
RIGGS: Pivot on the right,
kick with your left...

1468
01:16:03,812 --> 01:16:06,884
...and you whip that head around
to catch the target over there.

1469
01:16:06,972 --> 01:16:09,167
Like this. Get that head around
and follow through.

1470
01:16:09,252 --> 01:16:10,207
Like so.

1471
01:16:10,292 --> 01:16:11,850
So, you whip the head.

1472
01:16:13,212 --> 01:16:14,247
All right?

1473
01:16:14,812 --> 01:16:16,882
Thank you. Now you try it.

1474
01:16:17,772 --> 01:16:19,683
RIGGS: Here's your target. All right?

1475
01:16:19,772 --> 01:16:23,447
Remember, pivot right, kick left,
get that head around, spot that target.

1476
01:16:23,532 --> 01:16:26,046
ROGER: Like that.
RIGGS: Yeah. Follow the head around.

1477
01:16:26,132 --> 01:16:29,044
RIGGS: Back up a bit.
We don't want you to bump into the pole.

1478
01:16:29,132 --> 01:16:31,771
Just back up a little bit.
A little bit more. Okay, good.

1479
01:16:31,852 --> 01:16:33,922
Mind and body strong, now, grasshopper.

1480
01:16:34,012 --> 01:16:35,081
Okay.

1481
01:16:35,852 --> 01:16:36,807
Go.

1482
01:16:39,052 --> 01:16:40,849
[Hysterical laughter]

1483
01:16:44,292 --> 01:16:45,611
He can't hold his water.

1484
01:16:45,692 --> 01:16:47,171
Get back to work!

1485
01:16:47,532 --> 01:16:49,443
Okay, back to work everybody.

1486
01:16:49,612 --> 01:16:51,330
Oh, Rog, I'm sorry.

1487
01:16:51,412 --> 01:16:53,004
[Riggs laughing]

1488
01:16:53,732 --> 01:16:55,290
Sergeant Murtaugh?

1489
01:16:55,372 --> 01:16:59,809
You could be experiencing some
transitional anger caused by the shooting.

1490
01:17:00,612 --> 01:17:02,489
Do you want to talk about it?

1491
01:17:03,212 --> 01:17:05,567
- He's okay for a change.
- Are you sure?

1492
01:17:06,012 --> 01:17:08,810
You look good in red. That's your color.

1493
01:17:09,532 --> 01:17:12,490
- I've got a little extra time now.
- I'm fine.

1494
01:17:18,172 --> 01:17:19,207
Oh, shit!

1495
01:17:19,452 --> 01:17:21,204
Where's Sergeant Murtaugh?

1496
01:17:21,452 --> 01:17:22,567
RIGGS: What?

1497
01:17:22,652 --> 01:17:23,971
ROGER: It's her!

1498
01:17:24,092 --> 01:17:27,767
Can you tell me where I can find
the good-Iooking Sergeant Murtaugh?

1499
01:17:28,252 --> 01:17:29,480
DELORES: Hi, skinny!

1500
01:17:29,572 --> 01:17:32,132
DELORES: Delores. Remember me?
RIGGS: I remember you.

1501
01:17:32,212 --> 01:17:35,204
Can you tell me where I can find
the lovely Sergeant Murtaugh?

1502
01:17:35,292 --> 01:17:38,967
Actually, he's cowering down
on all fours right behind this counter.

1503
01:17:41,452 --> 01:17:44,489
DELORES: Where is the sergeant?
RIGGS: He's not here right now.

1504
01:17:44,572 --> 01:17:47,040
RIGGS: But he's talked of nothing
but you all week.

1505
01:17:47,132 --> 01:17:49,202
DELORES: Shut my mouth.
RIGGS: The man's on fire.

1506
01:17:49,292 --> 01:17:51,852
DELORES: What's the matter, baby?
RIGGS: A little sciatica.

1507
01:17:51,932 --> 01:17:54,492
DELORES: You tell him Delores was here.

1508
01:17:54,572 --> 01:17:56,244
You tell that man...

1509
01:17:56,372 --> 01:17:58,681
...that he's the jam in my jellyroll.

1510
01:17:59,492 --> 01:18:01,687
I'll see you, baby, okay. Bye-bye.

1511
01:18:02,572 --> 01:18:03,527
See you.

1512
01:18:05,172 --> 01:18:08,005
RIGGS: Delores says you're
"the jam in her jellyroll."

1513
01:18:08,092 --> 01:18:09,320
I heard!

1514
01:18:09,932 --> 01:18:11,843
RIGGS: That's a lot of woman.

1515
01:18:11,932 --> 01:18:15,607
She calls me all the time. She leaves me
notes. What am I going to do?

1516
01:18:15,692 --> 01:18:17,250
You shouldn't have led her on.

1517
01:18:17,332 --> 01:18:19,687
Led her on? I didn't do anything.

1518
01:18:23,332 --> 01:18:25,562
Sergeant, we have got to talk.

1519
01:18:25,972 --> 01:18:28,042
DOCTOR: You've got to come see me.

1520
01:18:28,732 --> 01:18:31,007
We've got to work. Come on. Let's go.

1521
01:18:31,292 --> 01:18:34,011
RIGGS: Thanks anyway, for your concern.
ROGER: Thanks, Doc.

1522
01:18:34,092 --> 01:18:35,286
ROGER: You're a beauty.
RIGGS: Coming?

1523
01:18:35,372 --> 01:18:37,442
ROGER: A real beauty. I'm coming.

1524
01:18:38,972 --> 01:18:40,724
[Car engine humming]

1525
01:18:44,412 --> 01:18:46,004
Good afternoon, Captain.

1526
01:18:47,972 --> 01:18:50,850
JACK: That's good, Murph.
See how easy that was?

1527
01:18:53,052 --> 01:18:54,531
[Tires squealing]

1528
01:18:54,612 --> 01:18:56,443
JACK: I love it down here. Don't you?

1529
01:18:56,532 --> 01:19:00,002
This place is better than the swap meet.
Best bargains in town.

1530
01:19:04,292 --> 01:19:05,361
COP: Give me the lock-up keys.

1531
01:19:06,572 --> 01:19:09,211
Those guys from the garage,
they're all ex-cons.

1532
01:19:09,292 --> 01:19:13,365
They were all busted by the same
police officer, Jack Edward Travis.

1533
01:19:13,532 --> 01:19:15,841
Early paroles on
the work-furlough program.

1534
01:19:15,932 --> 01:19:18,844
Employed by a company called
Mesa Verde Construction.

1535
01:19:19,212 --> 01:19:21,772
You can't go in there.
You don't have a pass.

1536
01:19:21,932 --> 01:19:23,684
- May I see your pass?
- My pass?

1537
01:19:23,772 --> 01:19:24,841
Here's my pass.

1538
01:19:24,932 --> 01:19:27,605
LEO: I got shot in the line of duty.
ROGER: He's with us.

1539
01:19:27,692 --> 01:19:29,284
- He's with us?
- I said that?

1540
01:19:29,372 --> 01:19:31,044
Where'd you get her from?

1541
01:19:31,212 --> 01:19:32,486
RIGGS: Why aren't you in the hospital?

1542
01:19:32,572 --> 01:19:33,846
Don't mention the hospital.

1543
01:19:33,932 --> 01:19:36,048
I told you not to leave me there.
They tried to take my appendix out.

1544
01:19:36,132 --> 01:19:37,645
LEO: They gave me a lapotomy.

1545
01:19:37,732 --> 01:19:39,723
- Brain surgery?
- A lapotomy.

1546
01:19:39,852 --> 01:19:42,127
Not a lobotomy.
Cut your hair so you can hear.

1547
01:19:42,212 --> 01:19:43,281
What's the difference?

1548
01:19:43,372 --> 01:19:47,126
The difference is, for a lapotomy,
they shave your nether regions.

1549
01:19:47,292 --> 01:19:48,407
Nether what?

1550
01:19:48,852 --> 01:19:50,729
Nether... I can't say it in front of her.

1551
01:19:50,812 --> 01:19:52,006
Point to it.

1552
01:19:53,212 --> 01:19:54,531
- Here.
- It must be itchy.

1553
01:19:54,612 --> 01:19:57,126
It is itchy. These doctors are savages.

1554
01:19:57,212 --> 01:20:00,648
Where does it say that a gunshot wound
requires a rectal exam?

1555
01:20:00,732 --> 01:20:02,245
LEO: Huh? Huh?

1556
01:20:02,892 --> 01:20:05,531
Yeah. With a telescope
big enough to see Venus.

1557
01:20:05,612 --> 01:20:07,170
I guess all they saw was Uranus.

1558
01:20:07,252 --> 01:20:09,243
That's great. Thank you.

1559
01:20:09,692 --> 01:20:11,125
LEO: You know what I say?

1560
01:20:11,212 --> 01:20:14,761
They fuck you in the hospital.
First they drug you, then they fuck you!

1561
01:20:14,852 --> 01:20:16,205
When they're done...

1562
01:20:16,292 --> 01:20:19,284
...the insurance company comes
and fucks you some more!

1563
01:20:19,412 --> 01:20:22,563
$10 for a fucking aspirin
and it isn't even covered!

1564
01:20:22,692 --> 01:20:23,761
That's enough!

1565
01:20:23,852 --> 01:20:25,444
We're trying to work here.

1566
01:20:25,532 --> 01:20:28,251
So, what's new on our case?
Anything new? You got Travis yet?

1567
01:20:28,332 --> 01:20:29,845
Did you guys advertise?

1568
01:20:29,932 --> 01:20:31,888
- He's family.
- Who's she?

1569
01:20:32,612 --> 01:20:34,921
- Sergeant Cole.
- How are you? Leo Getz.

1570
01:20:35,012 --> 01:20:36,604
Anything you need, Leo gets. Get it?

1571
01:20:36,692 --> 01:20:38,569
- I get it.
- It's real estate, now...

1572
01:20:38,652 --> 01:20:41,041
Listen, come on, you guys,
give me a break.

1573
01:20:41,132 --> 01:20:43,282
I owe this guy one.
Give me something to do.

1574
01:20:43,372 --> 01:20:45,010
You can get us a cup of coffee.

1575
01:20:45,092 --> 01:20:48,482
That's great. I take one for you
and that's what you tell me?

1576
01:20:48,772 --> 01:20:52,128
RIGGS: He could check this out.
LEO: That's all I'm good for?

1577
01:20:52,972 --> 01:20:54,325
We've got something for you to do.

1578
01:20:54,412 --> 01:20:58,246
Check out Mesa Verde Construction.
Find out all the information you can.

1579
01:20:58,852 --> 01:21:00,888
- Sure, I can do this.
- Can you remember that name?

1580
01:21:00,972 --> 01:21:02,485
Mesa Verde, I got it.

1581
01:21:02,652 --> 01:21:04,722
Wait, wait. What are you doing?

1582
01:21:04,812 --> 01:21:06,643
If there's any shit there, he'll find it.

1583
01:21:06,732 --> 01:21:07,926
LORNA: Who is that guy?
RIGGS: It's a long story.

1584
01:21:14,852 --> 01:21:16,683
Here are your keys, Captain.

1585
01:21:17,252 --> 01:21:18,241
You motherfucker!

1586
01:21:18,332 --> 01:21:19,845
- Don't be stupid.
- What the fuck?

1587
01:21:19,932 --> 01:21:23,925
Take the elevator, get the other guys.
Keys. Give me those fucking hands.

1588
01:21:24,652 --> 01:21:26,722
Goddamn you, Travis. Fuck.

1589
01:21:28,572 --> 01:21:29,971
Stand there.

1590
01:21:34,172 --> 01:21:36,732
I can get faster results than
that real estate broker.

1591
01:21:36,812 --> 01:21:39,246
RIGGS: Leo's not just a real estate broker.

1592
01:21:39,332 --> 01:21:42,404
ROGER: He's a pain in the ass
with a lot of connections.

1593
01:21:43,092 --> 01:21:46,323
JACK: This is what we came for.
Load everything on the elevator.

1594
01:21:46,412 --> 01:21:48,642
- How'd you know where to find them?
- We got it all, Jack.

1595
01:21:48,732 --> 01:21:50,882
The world of computers, Murph...

1596
01:21:50,972 --> 01:21:53,850
You used to be one of us, for Christ's sake.

1597
01:21:54,012 --> 01:21:56,651
You know what future a cop has? None.

1598
01:21:57,252 --> 01:22:00,005
Punch a clock for 30 years. Retirement.

1599
01:22:00,332 --> 01:22:01,560
Pension.

1600
01:22:02,052 --> 01:22:03,087
Nothing to do.

1601
01:22:03,172 --> 01:22:06,528
Drunk at noon, bullet in the brain
by evening. Not for this kid.

1602
01:22:06,612 --> 01:22:08,728
Police Department's got it all:

1603
01:22:08,812 --> 01:22:10,643
Guns, ammo, drugs, cash.

1604
01:22:10,732 --> 01:22:13,610
It's a one-stop shopping center
if you got the balls and the brains.

1605
01:22:13,692 --> 01:22:15,364
Not a thing anybody can do about it.

1606
01:22:15,452 --> 01:22:17,807
You're already fucking history
and you know it.

1607
01:22:17,892 --> 01:22:20,281
Sorry. I'm just getting started.

1608
01:22:20,892 --> 01:22:22,803
Something's wrong here.

1609
01:22:22,892 --> 01:22:25,326
The program's been accessed
by somebody from the outside.

1610
01:22:25,412 --> 01:22:27,004
What's been accessed?

1611
01:22:27,172 --> 01:22:30,448
After the guns were stolen, Internal Affairs
moved the confiscated ammunition.

1612
01:22:30,532 --> 01:22:31,442
Armor-piercing bullets?

1613
01:22:31,532 --> 01:22:34,171
Thousands of rounds
to a more secure location.

1614
01:22:35,612 --> 01:22:37,489
- That's what's been accessed.
- Someone else knows.

1615
01:22:37,572 --> 01:22:40,291
Where's this store? Where'd they move it?

1616
01:22:40,732 --> 01:22:42,006
LORNA: Let's go.

1617
01:22:42,572 --> 01:22:45,848
LORNA: I'm not cut out for Internal Affairs.
RIGGS: That's a switch.

1618
01:22:45,932 --> 01:22:47,524
LORNA: Right here in the building.
RIGGS: Where?

1619
01:22:47,612 --> 01:22:48,806
LORNA: I'm showing you.
COP: Something going down?

1620
01:22:48,892 --> 01:22:51,087
RIGGS: Nothing's going down.
COP: I'm going with you.

1621
01:22:51,172 --> 01:22:53,640
- How old are you?
- Twenty-two today.

1622
01:22:53,892 --> 01:22:54,847
Come on.

1623
01:22:55,012 --> 01:22:56,491
Have you got protection?

1624
01:22:56,572 --> 01:22:59,245
- Right here in my wallet.
- No, your vest, you dummy!

1625
01:22:59,332 --> 01:23:00,447
Should we take him?

1626
01:23:00,532 --> 01:23:03,649
- Okay, but keep your head down.
- Stay behind me.

1627
01:23:03,852 --> 01:23:05,922
RIGGS: Come on, let's go. Quiet!

1628
01:23:09,132 --> 01:23:11,930
[Dramatic instrumental music, background]

1629
01:23:17,772 --> 01:23:19,603
JACK: You were my ticket in.

1630
01:23:19,812 --> 01:23:22,451
JACK: It's too bad
you won't be coming with me.

1631
01:23:27,372 --> 01:23:29,010
LORNA: They got it all.

1632
01:23:29,892 --> 01:23:32,452
RIGGS: He's dead.
LORNA: How'd they get it out of here?

1633
01:23:32,532 --> 01:23:34,682
ROGER: I don't know.
RIGGS: Not upstairs.

1634
01:23:34,772 --> 01:23:36,091
ROGER: Elevator!

1635
01:23:39,012 --> 01:23:40,491
ROGER: Shit. It's down.

1636
01:23:40,572 --> 01:23:41,925
RIGGS: The subway's down there.

1637
01:23:42,012 --> 01:23:43,604
RIGGS: Let's take the stairs.
COP: LA has subways?

1638
01:23:43,692 --> 01:23:44,681
RIGGS: Where've you been?

1639
01:23:44,772 --> 01:23:45,921
ROGER: Read something
besides the comics.

1640
01:23:47,652 --> 01:23:50,086
JACK: All right. Come on, let's hustle!

1641
01:23:52,252 --> 01:23:53,685
Hurry up, guys.

1642
01:23:55,532 --> 01:23:56,851
[Clanking]

1643
01:24:02,452 --> 01:24:04,170
[Running footsteps]

1644
01:24:06,252 --> 01:24:07,685
LAPD! Come here!

1645
01:24:07,772 --> 01:24:09,728
RIGGS: Come here! Step on it!

1646
01:24:10,252 --> 01:24:11,765
Son of a bitch.

1647
01:24:11,892 --> 01:24:13,530
Did you see anybody or anything strange?

1648
01:24:13,612 --> 01:24:17,924
MAN: Lots of cops and a bunch of boxes.
RIGGS: Split now. Just get out of here.

1649
01:24:18,172 --> 01:24:20,561
RIGGS: I'm going across.
LORNA: I got it.

1650
01:24:20,772 --> 01:24:22,285
[Rapid gunfire]

1651
01:24:26,852 --> 01:24:28,763
JACK: Get rid of Murphy, now!

1652
01:24:34,132 --> 01:24:37,010
JACK: Where the fuck do you think
you're going? Let's go.

1653
01:24:37,092 --> 01:24:38,411
[Grunting]

1654
01:24:40,292 --> 01:24:41,805
[Roger gasping]

1655
01:24:42,572 --> 01:24:43,971
[Groaning and grunting]

1656
01:24:44,052 --> 01:24:46,088
[Crackling, man screaming]

1657
01:24:48,132 --> 01:24:49,963
JACK: Let's get out of here!

1658
01:24:51,172 --> 01:24:52,491
RIGGS: Cover me!

1659
01:24:54,412 --> 01:24:55,925
[Rapid gunfire]

1660
01:25:05,732 --> 01:25:07,688
[Cop screams and groans]

1661
01:25:11,932 --> 01:25:13,160
JACK: Let's go!

1662
01:25:22,972 --> 01:25:24,325
Stay still.

1663
01:25:33,972 --> 01:25:35,485
Happy birthday, kid.

1664
01:25:36,852 --> 01:25:38,365
[Rapid gunfire]

1665
01:26:00,652 --> 01:26:01,971
Another baby.

1666
01:26:14,372 --> 01:26:15,851
ROGER: Is he dead? Check the body.

1667
01:26:15,932 --> 01:26:16,842
MURPHY: Get me out of here!

1668
01:26:18,932 --> 01:26:20,729
Hey, Riggs! Hey, Riggs!

1669
01:26:20,812 --> 01:26:21,801
ROGER: Riggs!

1670
01:26:21,892 --> 01:26:23,371
Stupid son of a bitch!

1671
01:26:23,452 --> 01:26:25,170
[Running footsteps]

1672
01:26:25,932 --> 01:26:27,729
[Truck engine rumbling]

1673
01:26:27,852 --> 01:26:29,205
[Crackling]

1674
01:26:34,892 --> 01:26:35,881
Stop that!

1675
01:26:35,972 --> 01:26:36,927
Cut it out!

1676
01:26:37,012 --> 01:26:38,570
- Don't shoot!
- LAPD!

1677
01:26:38,972 --> 01:26:39,961
Where does this lead?

1678
01:26:40,052 --> 01:26:41,644
- Pico Station.
- Thanks.

1679
01:26:41,772 --> 01:26:42,841
MAN: Not that way.

1680
01:26:42,932 --> 01:26:45,127
Take the stairs, it's faster.

1681
01:26:45,532 --> 01:26:46,851
[Clanking]

1682
01:26:48,052 --> 01:26:50,850
[Dramatic instrumental music, background]

1683
01:26:56,252 --> 01:26:57,480
